title: tamale, corn, beans and frito casserole
directions: Put medium size package of corn chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then put can of pork and beans and same size can of cream-style corn on top of tamales.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° or 400° until all heated throughout (approximately 30 minutes).

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Pour squash mixture into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy; add oil, brown sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nutmeg together.
Add to batter with nuts and mix well.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a tester comes out dry and clean.

title: farmer's country breakfast
directions: In a skillet, brown and crumble sausage until fully cooked. Remove sausage; save drippings. In the drippings, cook potatoes and onion until potatoes are browned, stirring often. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, parsley and salt. Pour over potato mixture. Add sausage. Cook and stir gently over medium heat until eggs are set. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make
9-inch
pie shell.
Mix ingredients well and pour into crust.
Bake in oven at 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and place in jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Remove and discard onion.
Pour hot liquid over eggs.
Seal with an airtight lid. Refrigerate 2 days before using.
Will store up to 2 weeks.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all together by hand and form into ball.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sweet breaded chicken
directions: In a saucepan, heat 1 cup milk, 1 tablespoon butter and 4 tablespoons syrup.
Mix to blend.
Don't boil, warm mixture.
Add chicken breasts.
Cover with liquid.
Simmer for several minutes.

title: "easy as pie" spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pie crust in pie dish to line bottom and sides of pie dish.
Cook frozen creamed spinach following package directions; pour into bowl.
Whisk together the eggs.
Add eggs to spinach mixture, then add Swiss cheese.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve as a side dish or with a Greek salad for lunch.

title: molasses cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg and molasses until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet; set aside.

title: mushroom cheese canapes
directions: Mix together shredded cheese, chopped mushrooms, olives, onions, cream in mayonnaise.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or you may broil them.

title: steak sauce
directions: Put onion and oil in saucepan over low heat and cook slow until the onion is soft.
Mash up the onion with a metal spoon, then add the remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Let the sauce get cool before pouring into jar.
Keep unused portion in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: capellini pomodoro
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions; keep warm. Meanwhile mince garlic and basil.
Set each aside.
Seed and dice tomatoes.
Grate Parmesan cheese; heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook until it turns white.
Add tomatoes and pepper and heat through, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes.
Tomatoes should not lose their shape.
Remove from heat. Transfer hot, cooked pasta to large bowl.
Toss pasta gently with tomato mixture, basil and half the Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately and pass remaining Parmesan cheese.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place broken taco shells in bottom.
Layer the chicken on top.
Combine soup, onion, tomatoes and 1/2 of the cheese in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix and roll in balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm, then roll in powdered sugar again when cool.

title: fettuccine
directions: Cook noodles 7 minutes. Set aside in glass bowl. Heat cheese, butter and cream 2 1/2 minutes or until butter is melted, stirring twice. Stir in cooked noodles; toss well. Season with pepper.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until tender.
Mix other ingredients, except cheese, and pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese immediately after removing from oven.

title: turkey and cheese wedges
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, oregano, fennel seed and garlic until turkey is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
In a medium bowl, stir together eggs, Ricotta cheese, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Spread over turkey mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is set.
Arrange tomatoes atop casserole; sprinkle with American cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes. Cool and chop.
Chop onion and eggs.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, mustard and salt and pepper until smooth. Mix all together and refrigerate several hours.
You may add celery and radishes, if you wish.

title: krispies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt and soda.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until fully combined.
Add flour mixture, rice cereal and chocolate chunks.
Blend at low speed until combined. Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately transfer cookies to a cool, flat surface.

title: leftover meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust. Combine meat, gravy, vegetables and potatoes and place in crust. Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: easy potato dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add chopped onion, salt, pepper, melted butter, Parmesan cheese and dots of butter on top.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift the flour with the salt, sugar and baking powder. Rub in the shortening. Beat the egg until light, without separating.
Add the milk and pour it into the flour.
Beat thoroughly. Add cherries and pour at once into a shallow greased pan. Bake 30 minutes in a hot oven. Serve hot with sugar and cream.

title: baked zucchini with tomatoes
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, garlic, tomatoes, salt, pepper, parsley and oregano.
Place in casserole and pour olive oil over top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat eggs; add oil.
Stir in strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 baby loaves.

title: pepperoni tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease miniature muffin tins (2).
Mix all of the
ingredients.
Fill muffin tins to make 24 tarts.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together well and put on bottom of a round plate with an edge.
Spread cocktail sauce over cheese mixture and place shrimp on top.
Serve with desired choice of crackers.

title: campers chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
Divide and store in jars.
Use 1/3 cup mixture to 2/3 cup hot water.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cube Velveeta and put in crock-pot with slab (approximately 2 tablespoons) butter and let melt.
Add small jar of chunky salsa, mild or medium, thin with milk.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Roll into balls.
Put ball on ungreased cookie sheet.
Push Kiss in middle of each.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let stand on sheet 5 minutes before removing to plate or cooking rack.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute onion in butter; add vinegar, then the brown sugar, lemon juice, catsup, stock or hot water, celery, salt and Worcestershire.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add water or more stock, if necessary.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Pour syrup in jug. Add 1 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Add 1 gallon water and 2 (2 liter) drinks.

title: one dish pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
In the meantime mix soups, water, pepper, and rice in a casserole dish. Add browned pork chops and cook covered in the preheated oven for 45 min.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed; do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until it springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: roasted potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Pat noodles dry with paper towel.
Place olive oil in the bottom of a large bowl and toss potatoes until covered with a coating of oil. Prepare jelly roll pan or cookie sheet by covering with foil, shiny side up.
Spray with cooking spray.
Place potatoes evenly on foil.
Do not overlap.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, about 112 calories per 3 wedges.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, peppers and garlic in butter.
Add liquid from tomatoes, salt, flour and water.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, sugar and wine; cook for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Garnish with oranges and cherries.
Serves 50.

title: senator bean soup
directions: Simmer for 3 hours and then add braised onion. Season with salt and pepper.

title: blackened fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a small mixing bowl combine onion powder, garlic salt, red pepper, basil, white pepper, thyme, black pepper and sage.
Brush both sides of fish with melted margarine; coat with seasoning.
If using a charcoal grill, remove grill rack and place an unoiled 12-inch cast-iron skillet directly on hot coals.
If using a gas grill, turn to high and place skillet on the grill rack.
Preheat the skillet 5 minutes or until a drop of water sizzles.
Add coated fillets to skillet.
Carefully drizzle about 2 teaspoons of melted margarine over the fish.
Grill fish 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until blackened.
Turn fish and drizzle with 2 teaspoons of melted margarine.
Grill 2 1/2 to 3 minutes more.
Transfer to serving plates.
Drizzle with any remaining melted margarine. Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut flake cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
After baked, punch holes with wooden spoon handle in cake.
Pour Coco Lopez over cake.
Let cool. After cool, add Cool Whip until covered. Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Mix vegetables, potato soup, 1/2 cup milk and chicken in bowl.
Pour into pie shells.
Place the Pillsbury pie crust over top of pie shell and pinch sides to close on each pie.
Beat egg; rub egg lightly over each pie crust top to give shiny effects.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Blend 1/2 of this in your processor.
Recombine the two batches.
Add 1/3 cup olive oil, 3 tablespoons cider vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Other additions are Tabasco, diced jalapeno, chopped green chiles or red pepper flakes.
Chill very thoroughly.
Serve with an ice cube in each bowl.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar with small amount of water over low heat until sugar has melted.
Add almonds and stir until well coated.
Cook, then break apart.
Store at room temperature.
In large bowl, place lettuce, spinach, celery and onions. Immediately before serving, toss with Sweet-Sour Dressing.
Then add mandarin oranges and almonds.
Don't add Sweet-Sour Dressing until ready to serve; it will make the salad soggy.

title: cheese custard(flan)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
In a solid cake pan, melt 4 to 5 tablespoons of sugar until caramel forms.
Tilt pan so as to spread caramel to cover the sides.
Pour mixture and place the cake pan in another pan containing 1/2-inch of water. (This is called bano Maria, similar to double boiling).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove and separate edges and cool overnight.
Invert into a platter for serving so that caramel doesn't spill.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill 2 hours.
You may freeze and keep indefinitely.

title: mom's fruit slush
directions: Boil 2 cups water and sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, juice and fruit.
Put in freezer containers.
Stir occasionally until frozen.
Keep until frozen.
Thaw some before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly oil, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler with tomato soup.
Soak gelatin in cold water. Add gelatin to soup and cheese mixture, mixing well. Cool.
Add mayonnaise and vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and chilies; season with garlic salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Warm soups together and mix with meat. Layer Doritos with meat and cheese.
Heat in oven to melt top layer of cheese.
Add jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: granny's cornmeal chess pie
directions: Mix cornmeal and sugar.
Mix margarine until blended.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan well.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into pan and smooth the top.
Cover with buttered foil and bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for an additional 15 minutes to allow the top to brown. Serves 4.

title: pecan pie(1930)
directions: Cream butter, then add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy. Add slightly beaten eggs and other ingredients.
When all ingredients have been stirred up, pour mixture into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This makes 3 pies.

title: grammy's cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese gradually.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: seared salmon
directions: Cut salmon into steaks. Marinate for 30 minutes. Dry on paper towels. Sprinkle with crushed peppercorn. Put small amount of cooking oil in skillet. Fry, skin side up. Flip 1 time (approximately 2 minutes per side). Puncture with knife. When knife slides through easily, it's done.

title: caramel ice cream dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with pastry blender.
Spread out on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown (15 to 20 minutes).
Cool.
Crumble all of the baked mixture.
Place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle 1/2 of caramel; put remaining crumbs aside.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of crumbled mixture layer.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 jar of caramel.
Cover with foil and freeze.

title: apple cake(diabetic)
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 package Equal in small saucepan. Simmer over medium heat until all water is absorbed.
In large bowl, combine oil, apple, applesauce, eggs, prunes, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla and 8 packages Equal.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to batter.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is light brown.

title: potluck cake
directions: Spread pineapple in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Crumble cake mix evenly over pineapple; sprinkle with almonds.
Dot evenly with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken bombay(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown chicken in seasoned flour and butter.
Arrange chicken in a flat baking dish.
Combine all ingredients except cornstarch and sour cream and olives.
Cover; bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, until tender.
Remove chicken; place on a serving platter.
Stir cornstarch into liquid in baking dish.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in olives and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Serve with Uncle Ben's long grain and wild rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cooked peaches. Do not stir!
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: onion quiche pie(no dairy products)
directions: Whiz 1 cup water with cashews.
Add onion and garlic powders, tofu, lemon juice, salt and basil to blender and whiz.
Saute chopped onion in 2 tablespoons water.
Add this plus green onion to mixture from blender.

title: greek shrimp
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onion and garlic in a small amount of olive oil until onion is softened.
Add the tomatoes and break them up with a large spoon.
Add the wine and let that cook.
Next, add half the oregano and continue cooking about 20 minutes.
It should thicken nicely.
At this point, the sauce can be covered and refrigerated until nearly time to serve.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on cocktail rye bread.
Top with slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with dill weed. Chill and serve.

title: eggplant parmigiana(4 servings)
directions: Heat margarine in medium saucepan; saute onion and garlic until onion is golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Wash eggplant.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine flour, seasoned salt and pepper to coat eggplant.
Place 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet and saute eggplant slices, a few at a time.
Add more oil, if needed.
Set slices aside as they soften and brown.
Preheat oven to 350°.
*Sprinkle ground beef with salt (optional).
Gently shape into 8 patties about 1/2-inch thick. Broil 4-inches from heat, 5 minutes on each side.
Spoon half of the sauce into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer eggplant and meat in dish.
Spoon on remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan; top with sliced Mozzarella.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes or just until Mozzarella is melted and golden.

title: hickory smoke meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Press into 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Spread additional barbecue sauce over top of loaf.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Start with custard, wafers and banana.
Reserve 2 tablespoons sugar.
In top of double boiler, combine remaining sugar, flour and salt.
Beat in 1 whole egg and 3 yolks.
Reserve 3 egg whites. Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in vanilla.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip and cool.

title: banana-orange cream
directions: Place half of bananas, lemon juice, ginger, orange juice concentrate and milk in food processor or blender.
Whirl at high speed until well blended and smooth.
Pour into serving pitcher. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately or refrigerate covered up to 3 hours.
Whisk to blend before serving.

title: au gratin vegetable dish
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and onion in margarine.
Slowly add flour, vegetable liquid, salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Cook until thickened and cheese melts.
Pour some of the cheese sauce into a 10 x 6-inch baking pan. Top with vegetables.
Pour remaining sauce over. Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Can be warmed in oven or broiled 4-inches from heat for a few minutes or until top is lightly brown.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the water, butter and oatmeal together and let it stand for 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken gourmet bake(serves 6)
directions: Mix together chicken soup and milk.
Mix together dressing and oleo or butter.
Place breasts in a flat baking dish.
Place a cheese slice on each breast, cover with soup mix, then cover with dressing mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream ingredients.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Cut water chestnuts in half and roll up in bacon. Seal them with a toothpick. Place in a casserole dish. Mix chili sauce, Miracle Whip and brown sugar together in a bowl. Pour over water chestnuts and bacon; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Ad sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Stir to blend.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: country captain
directions: Remove skin from the chicken pieces and coat with mixture of next three ingredients.
Cook in fat in heavy skillet, browning on all sides.
Remove chicken and keep hot.
Cook onions, pepper and garlic in the same skillet, stirring until lightly browned.
Mix the next ingredients with the tomatoes and simmer (this can be done first, if you like, while the other is cooking).

title: doreen's corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well and add liquid ingredients, except for butter.
Mix.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Immediately after coming out of oven, drizzle 1 block melted butter over.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and dressing mix.
Then add all ingredients, including the liquid from the cans.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Garnish with taco chips and grated cheese.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir.	Cool
a little; add cherry pie mix, chopped apples, celery
and
chopped nuts. Mix and let set up.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: crunchy snack
directions: Pour dressing mix into oil, then pour over crackers.
Stir about every 15 minutes for 6 to 8 hours.

title: oppossum with sweet potatoes
directions: Skin and clean opossum, removing small sacs from small of back and under forelegs.
Place opposum in 4 cups water in saucepan; add salt, pepper and red peppers.
Simmer until pot liquid is reduced by half.
Pare and slice sweet potatoes.
Combine opposum with pan liquid and potatoes in baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until opposum is tender.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix the flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix all together. Add the chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Make into golf ball size cookies.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Beat all together until smooth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Add broccoli to pan. Spread evenly.
Slice up 1 stick of butter and spread evenly over broccoli.
Slice cheese and lay over butter.
Spread crackers over cheese.
Melt remaining butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: nanny's stuffed green peppers
directions: In bowl combine garlic, oregano, raisins, anchovies, oil and vinegar.
Stuff each pepper with filling.
Place saved top on top of pepper.
Place peppers in large pan so they stay upright.
Pour a little oil, vinegar, sugar and water (approximately 1 to 2 inches) in pan.
Cover and bring to boil, then simmer until tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Save juice to pour over peppers.
Dip bread in excess juice.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes. Place in a greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars; beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Melt cheese until smooth and add rice. Pour into casserole or serving dish.
No need for additional baking.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thick slice from stem end of pepper. Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Lightly stuff each pepper.
Stand peppers upright in greased baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Season with garlic salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain liquid off.
Mix with cream cheese.
Roll bread flat; cut off crusts.
Spread mixture on bread and roll up.
Cut into thirds.
Dip in butter and put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: In heavy pan, melt butter; add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook on medium heat to 300°.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/4 cups nuts.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Lay chocolate bars on top.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts on top.
Crack in pieces when cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Use little cupcake cups or spray tins with Pam.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Top
each chicken breast with ham and cheese. Roll up and secure each with toothpicks. Brush with oil and roll in bread crumbs.
Place roll-ups on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, miniature marshmallows and peanuts.
Stir until marshmallows are coated. Pour in buttered cookie sheet.

title: maxine's red velvet cake
directions: Cream
the
sugar
and butter.	Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Make
paste
from
cocoa and vinegar and add to butter mixture. Sift salt, soda and flour together and add to mixture and buttermilk.
Add
vanilla	and coloring.
Makes 3 layers. Grease and flour pans and add cake mixture. Bake at 350°.

title: slow cooked sour cream pot roast
directions: In a skillet, cook the bacon until crisp, drain, reserving the dripping.
Crumble the bacon, wrap and refrigerate.
Trim the fat from the Roast, cut the roast in half to fit into a slow cooker or crock pot.
In the skillet brown the meat in the bacon drippings, drain and place in the slow cooker.
Stir together onion, water, salt, bay leaf, cumin and pepper, pour over the meat.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove roast, discard Bay leaf.
Skim the fat from the liquid, pour liquid into a saucepan.
Return the roast to the slow cooker, cover.
Blend sour cream and flour, stir into the hot liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened, DO NOT BOIL.
Stir in parsley and Kitchen Bouquet to taste.
Serve meat garnished with bacon.
Serve gravy over the Hot cooked Noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute ground chuck; add Ro-Tel tomatoes and kidney beans and simmer.
Mix rice into meat mixture.
Grate cheese into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with Fritos.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: california gold cheese ball
directions: Place cream cheese in food processor; blend until smooth.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Blend until very smooth and golden in color. Form ball; roll in sunflower seeds.
Wrap in Saran and refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: fresh strawberry cooler
directions: Place strawberries, honey and 1/2 the milk in blender.
Puree until almost smooth.
Add remaining milk and ice cream.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in tall glasses.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: sophie's country apple cake
directions: Use 11 x 16-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter and beaten eggs.
Stir until soft dough is formed.
Spread in greased pan.
Put apples on top and sprinkle with crumb topping. Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chicken thighs supreme
directions: Put chicken in large pot.
Add onions, vinegar, garlic, celery salt, pepper, water and bay leaf.
Cover and cook 1 hour over medium heat.
Check during cooking and add additional water, if needed.
Halfway through cooking, add potato.

title: flaming frangelico
directions: Scoop out 2 servings of ice cream.
Set bowl onto saucer and pour on two shot glasses of Frangelico liqueur over the ice cream. Light a match when serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add baking powder, salt and flour until desired consistency.
Fry in lightly greased skillet until set. Serve with choice of syrup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions; drain.
Mix with other ingredients, except dressing.
Melt 1 stick margarine with dressing.
Put half of dressing on bottom and then pour in squash mixture.
Then put rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes after rolling out and cutting biscuits with a cookie cutter.
Dough will keep in the refrigerator if you make it ahead of time.
Does not have to rise before you bake it.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat egg; add milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
This should be like a muffin mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange sliced peaches, which have been peeled, on top in rows.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with powdered sugar.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Stir in flour until smooth; remove from heat.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Spread on an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (golden brown).
Mix the cream cheese with milk.
Add pudding mix; beat until thick.
Spread over crust.
Cover with Cool Whip; drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: meal gravy
directions: Melt bacon grease in iron skillet.
Add meal and stir constantly until golden brown. Add milk, slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, adding more milk if necessary. Add black pepper.

title: melitzanes papoutsakia l'odeon
directions: Cut eggplants in half.
Scoop out pulp and chop.
Save shells. Saute chopped onions in butter until golden.
Add eggplant; cook for 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl and cool.
Stir in crumbled Feta cheese, Parmesan cheese, milk mixed with egg, chopped parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff shells; top with sliced tomatoes. Sprinkle with olive oil.
Arrange in lightly oiled shallow pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then cut oven to 325° and bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and let start to jell, then beat in Cool Whip.
Add by folding pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Place back in refrigerator and let jell.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make sauce of first 5 ingredients.
Add cheese.
Place half of potatoes in a greased casserole (2-quart).
Cover with half the onion and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: cream cheese vegetable sandwiches
directions: Drain all vegetables well!
Mix well the drained vegetables, softened cream cheese, cheese, mayonnaise and salt. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: auntie corine's wonderful brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together; cool.
Blend eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add chocolate mixture and walnuts.
Bake on a large cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling and spread.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of pineapple and cherries.
Cut margarine into thin slices and lay over the cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet and saute zucchini and onion until tender. Remove from heat.
Mix together eggs and cheese, then add spices.
Line 10-inch pie plate with rolls to make crust and spread with mustard.
Mix zucchini and onion with egg mixture; pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: roast beef 'n swiss tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon salad dressing on each tortilla, covering entire surface.
Top each with lettuce leaf and half of roast beef, cheese and onion.
Roll up each tortilla tightly.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Take from heat.
Add a few drops of red food coloring and 2 tablespoons of strawberry jello; pour over strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Chill for 1 hour and serve with whipped cream.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken; bake 1 hour until done at 350°.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half; clean and boil in lightly salted water until tender, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onions, chopped bell peppers and celery for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add ground meat and season with the garlic salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, seasoned salt and red pepper.
Drain excess grease, then add sherry, tomatoes, eggs, cheese and bread crumbs.
Stuff into individual bell pepper shells and bake at 350° for 20 minutes until firm.
Serves 10.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast in water.
Add desired seasoning.
Reserve 2 cups broth.
Cool breast enough to handle, discard bone and skin.
Tear chicken in pieces and place in buttered casserole (1 stick).
Combine soups and milk, pour over chicken.
Melt 3/4 stick of butter in broth and add to stuffing mix, blending lightly.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage; cut pepper and onion in rings.
Slice tomatoes; dice celery and combine all ingredients in a large skillet (electric is nice).
Cover and cook on medium heat until crisp and tender, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Leftovers keep well.

title: husbands delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat through a colander.
Return meat to pan and add tomato sauce.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Chop green onions.
Mix together 1 1/2 pkg. of the cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well by hand; do not use a blender.
Add green onions.
Set aside. Boil noodles according to pkg directions.
Drain well.
In large casserole dish begin layering ingredients beginning with sauce, noodles, more sauce and then cream cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Cook in oven at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Add cheddar cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onion together and drain well.
Add tomato soup and 1/2 can of water.
Stir in chili powder and cook with beef until thickened.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Put cooked spaghetti in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour sauce over spaghetti; spread on celery soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom soup

title: "best" banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 2 greased bread pans at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients in 3-inch deep 9 x 13-inch dish; do not mix.
Spread mayonnaise and sugar mixture over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and chopped, hard-cooked egg, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper.
Cook green pepper in fat until tender.
Mix green pepper, corn, crackers, milk, salt, pepper and egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Arrange bacon on top of mixture and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, then eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased tube pan.
Put ground nuts in bottom of pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain and chill.
Drain
shrimp
and add to macaroni.
Combine green pepper, onion
and celery.	Add to macaroni.
Add salad dressing and mayonnaise.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: ground beef appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand, breaking up any large chunks of cheese.
Spread evenly, not thick, to edges of rye bread.
Put under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly.
The crusts burn easily, so watch carefully.
Serve immediately.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: curry seafood salad
directions: Add rice and salt to boiling water; stir to moisten all rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, then uncover and let cool to room temperature.

title: special cheese dip
directions: Brown meat thoroughly.
Drain grease.
Add salt and pepper. Add melted Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel.

title: quick beef minestrone soup
directions: In 3 quart pan, combine water, vegetables, tomatoes, pasta, bouillon and basil.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes until pasta is tender.
Stir beef into simmering soup.
Immediately remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Set aside popped popcorn in a large metal bowl.
Mix butter, Karo syrup, brown sugar and salt together and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, not stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda; pour over corn in bowl.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: dream bars
directions: Combine cake, eggs and butter.
Press mixture on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar with cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400°
until brown.
Stir and rebake until brown again.
Remove from oven; cool and serve.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix mayo and sugar.
Put in layers with mayonnaise in the middle and on top.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Beat the mixture vigorously by hand until tacky.
Drop by teaspoons onto buttered wax paper.
Cool until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, salt, oil and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until completely combined.
Stir in remaining 3 1/2 cups of flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Make into rolls and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, green pepper, water, mushrooms, salt, sugar, chili powder or oregano and spaghetti (broken into 2-inch pieces).
Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375°, stirring occasionally until spaghetti is tender, about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Cheddar or processed American cheese.
Return to oven, uncovered, and bake until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate-mint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, 1/2 cup margarine (butter), the vanilla, egg and unsweetened chocolate.
Stir in flour and salt. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until set, about 8 minutes.
Cool cookies completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut noels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine brown sugar, peanut butter, shortening, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg; beat until just blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until just blended.
Drop by spoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross with fork.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Transfer to foil to cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix the eggs, butter and buttermilk well.
Add the remaining ingredients, except prunes.
Mix well.
Add the prunes.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: cafe au lait mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 cups mix.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Cook in an iron skillet, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add extra milk if filling is too thick.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients together until smooth and creamy. Use all the fruit to dip into mixture like a fondue.
This dip can also be used as a topping on fresh fruit or strawberry shortcake. Trust me; it's great!

title: vegetable saute
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet and add carrots, squash, onion, eggplant and yellow pepper.
Saute, stirring and tossing, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook, again tossing and stirring, about 3 minutes.
Add basil.
Stir to combine.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: italian vegetable soup(slow-cooker)
directions: Layer in slow-cooker (in order) carrots, onion, celery, potatoes, parsley, garlic, bouillon, basil, salt, pepper and kidney beans with liquid.
Add water.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or low for 8 to 9 hours.
Stir in stewed tomatoes with juice and ham.
Immediately cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Mix fruit and nuts with part of flour to coat.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then add flavoring.
Mix batter with fruit and nuts.
Chill overnight. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Put pan of water in bottom of oven while cooking.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Mix well and chill about 1 hour. Shape in small balls and press in muffin pans.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Cook potatoes in jacket; peel and grate.
Chop onion and cook in butter.
Mix potatoes, onion, sour cream, cheese and soup together.
Put in pan and put buttered corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Allow 1 hour preparation time.

title: broccoli, rice and chicken casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli and melt cheese over it.
Bake chicken breasts.
Season with lemon pepper, salt and poultry seasoning.
Cut into small pieces after cooked.
Cook rice.
Combine all in a large casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup and celery or mushroom soup.
Add enough water to be smooth.
Stir this into the casserole.
Bake at 350° until top turns golden.
Top with Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream in a large bowl.
Add thawed berries (strain some juice out of the berries as it may be quite runny).
Pour into baked pie shell.
Freeze overnight.

title: mom broussard's bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, salt, sugar, milk, pineapple and coconut.
Pour over bread; mix well.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stromboli(garbage bread)
directions: Divide one bread dough loaf in half.
On floured surface, roll out to 9-inch square.
Cover dough with layers of any or all of the listed ingredients.
Roll in tight jelly roll fashion, pinching seam and ends.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Mix together and melt the peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine until smooth.
Pour this mixture over the cereal and stir together.
Pour the powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Pour cereal in bag and shake it up.
Store in airtight container.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix altogether and bake in greased pan at 350° until brown.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll pieces of chicken in dry bread crumbs. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes. Take out and add sauce over the top.
Add cheese.
Cook 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven
to
Mix
bran, sugar, flour, soda, spice and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix
well.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake in a 400° oven
for
15 to 20 minutes.
Store rest of batter in refrigerator.
Can be
kept up to 6 weeks in covered container.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Place all ingredients in a large casserole dish and bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and let cheese melt.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms in 1 inch of water with 1 teaspoon of salt for 5 minutes.
Cool mushrooms before adding other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Turn jar frequently to marinate.
May want to double recipe; it goes fast!

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham
crackers	and
melt oleo.
Mix with sugar and press in
cake pan.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on packages.
Mix cream
cheese in the Dream Whip and spread on crumbs. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: mimi's spinach parmesan
directions: Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze dry. Chop until there are no large stems. Put in mixing bowl. Tear bread into small pieces and add with all other ingredients. Blend well. Put in lightly buttered baking dish. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cornbread dressing for 100
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar and seasonings.
Add onion; toss.
Add milk and eggs.
Blend well.
Pour into hot greased pans.
Bake at 425° until browned; cool.
Crumble and let dry.
Add sage and poultry seasoning and pepper to taste.
Saute in butter the celery until tender.
Add chopped onions and celery to bread crumbs and toss.
Add broth to bread crumbs to make very moist.
Bake in large pan 30 to 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: madeleines
directions: You will need a Madeleine mold and a pastry bag.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease mold pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Scald milk; let cool.
Add yeast to warm water.
Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add to milk.
Mix flour and salt with other ingredients, forming a soft dough.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Melt the butter.
Combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Dip walnut-size balls of dough in melted butter, roll in sugar mixture.
Drop in a greased angel food pan.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn out on plate.
Pull balls off when ready to serve.

title: sugar-free chocolate drizzle
directions: Blend cornstarch, water and salt in saucepan and add chocolate.
Cook on low heat until chocolate melts and add rest of ingredients.
Serve over cake or ice cream.
Yields 1/3 cup.

title: georgia's cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 cup nuts.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball, then roll in the reserved nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix orange drink and condensed milk thoroughly.
Add pineapple.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: chocolate chess pies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
For chocolate lovers only! Very rich!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; slice half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; add mayonnaise and stir well.
Add relish, mustard, salt and pepper; stir well.
Spoon yolk mixture into a decorating bag fitted with a large star tip.
Pipe yolk mixture into egg whites.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Top each stuffed egg with an olive slice and a sprig of parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and peanut butter.
Add the brown sugar and white sugar; beat.
Beat in the egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in the flour, soda and salt.
Shape by teaspoon into balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and add a chocolate candy kiss.
Press down so that cookie cracks around the edges.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes, until done.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside. Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers; cook 5 minutes and drain.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Using a meat grinder, grind the first 4 ingredients. Add the sugar.
Mix well. Store in glass jar in refrigerator.
Will last for a couple of months. May be frozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Stir. Pour mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter.
Combine 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Add to peaches.
Spoon peach mixture over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes or until brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: First, use one cup of flour to roll the nuts and raisins in so they will not sink to the bottom.
Mix all ingredients (in the order listed) and pour into a 13x9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 - 1 3/4 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken, onion, carrot, celery and salt in enough water to cover, about 2 hours.
Remove chicken and when cool, remove skin and bones; dice meat.
Strain stock and, if necessary, add enough water to make 1 quart.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour mixed with paprika.
Add chicken stock gradually, stirring constantly; cook for 2 minutes.
Add cream, pepper and adjust seasoning to taste.
Spoon Dumplings on top of gently bubbling chicken mixture and cover.
Cook 15 minutes without lifting lid. Serve at once.

title: ginny's extremely easy potato salad
directions: Microwave small red potatoes until done.
Cool.
Cut into quarters.
Add mayonnaise until coated.
Add 2 to 3 packets Good Seasons Italian dressing mix (dry).
Let sit (refrigerate) for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Knead as long as it takes to mix ingredients.
Roll real thin and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: original toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cucumber stick pickles
directions: Wash and cut small cucumbers into eighths.
Pour boiling water over them and leave overnight.
Next morning, drain and pack in jars.

title: minced meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, ham, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape mixture into 6 dozen tiny meatballs. Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until done at 375°.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, combine pie filling, juice and vinegar; heat until bubbly. Add meatballs.
Keep warm, adding juice if becomes too thick.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Pour oil over spaghetti and toss. Mix soups and milk.
Stir meat, mushrooms, peppers and olives. Stir in spaghetti.
Pour into a casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds during last 10 minutes of baking.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place in greased baking dish, either canned or home cooked apples.
Mix together all ingredients with a fork until crunchy and sprinkle over apples.
Pour over all melted butter or oleo. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute 1/4 c chopped onion and 1/4 c bell pepper in 2 tsp oil. Add 1 c boiling water mied with 1 pkg ranch dressing mix.
Add can of mushrooms, 1 can rtoel tomatoes, prepared chicken, and velveeta. Heat 5 minutes to let cheese melt; mix well.
Layer mixture with 2 cups cooked spaghetti in a 8 x8 sprayed dish.
Cook 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese cake(high cholesterol)
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter, walnuts and cinnamon and place in bottom of cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in frypan.
Line casserole dish with chicken. Sprinkle grated cheese over the chicken.
Top with Stove Top stuffing, prepared as to package directions.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in the shortening.
Add buttermilk and the yeast, dissolved in water.
Mix with a spoon until all flour is moist.
Cover the bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Can also be used right away.
The dough will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: loempias(indonesian egg rolls)
directions: Fry chicken, onion and leek.
Add soy sauce, bean sprouts and garlic powder (add a little more oil if necessary).
Fry until bean sprouts are getting translucent, but not limp.
Add ham and let cool.
Make a smooth batter with flour, water and egg white.
Heat a generous amount of oil or butter in an omelet pan, over a low fire.
Place 1/2 of batter in pan, a little at a time, to make 6 crepes.
Only fry one side of the crepes.
Put 1/2 of the filling on fried side of crepes and fold crepes like envelopes, gluing with a mixture of water and flour.
Fry the loempias in generous hot oil in wok or big frying pan until they are brown on both sides. Serves 6. Delicious with sweet and sour sauce or peanut butter sauce.

title: flaky squares
directions: Mix Crisco, salt and 1/2 of water.
Add flour and rest of water, a little at a time.
Roll out thin layer of dough and spread with filling of your choice as much as you like.
Put another crust on top.
Prick with a fork all over and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until done, like for a pie.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a full boil that you cannot stir down.
Take off stove. Add peanut butter. Stir until melted. Add Special K cereal.
Mix well. Spoon on wax paper. Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine. Grease a large casserole dish and place mixture in it. Mix bread crumbs and margarine together and put on top of mixture. Place in 350° oven. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cheese crusted flank steak
directions: Combine red wine, oil, vinegar, garlic and oregano in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Add flank steaks. Marinate 24 to 48 hours in refrigerator.

title: diabetic luncheon - turkey divan
directions: In advance, prepare mornay sauce, cook broccoli and cut turkey in thick (1/4-inch ) slices.

title: stuffed cornish game hens
directions: Prepare your favorite stuffing mix (uncooked).
Set aside. Clean the game hens, rinse and pat dry with paper towel.
Rub cavities with seasoned salt; rub outer skin with Cajun seasoning. Lightly fill cavities with the stuffing.
Put game hens, breast side up, on rack in roasting pan; brush with melted butter or margarine.
Roast, uncovered, at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until hens test done.
Remove and serve.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Stir in paprika, cumin, mustard, garlic powder, chili powder, milk, jalapeno pepper and sauce; blend thoroughly.
Add cheese gradually, stirring, until mixture is smooth.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and nutmeg, then sift together twice.
Cream butter, adding sugar gradually, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, lemon rind and cream or milk; beat well.
Roll into a thin sheet on slightly floured board.
Cut with floured cutter and dredge with sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 7 minutes.
This makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies, 3-inches in diameter. These may also be cut into fancy shapes and sprinkled with colored sugar.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Combine garlic, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar in a bowl.
Add mushrooms and allow to marinate for 3 hours, basting quite frequently.
Drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in the skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook over high heat for 1 minute. Reduce the heat to low and cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place mushrooms in a well buttered dish.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top of the mushrooms and dot with the remaining butter.
Bake for 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: pineanna nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three round 9-inch cake pans.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat).
Stir in bananas, pecans, vanilla and pineapple.
Divide batter and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Let set until sugar melts. Sift all dry ingredients.
Blend eggs and butter.
Add apples and sugar mixture, then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: three cheese lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger. Cook 10 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles per directions on box. With a lasagna pan or 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1 row of lasagna noodles on bottom of pan.
Put 1 layer of spaghetti sauce over that.
Add 1 layer of Mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Add 1 layer of noodles over that.
Put 1 layer of sauce over that.
Put 1 layer of Ricotta cheese on that.
Put 1 layer of noodles over that.
Put 1 layer of spaghetti sauce on noodles.
Add 1 layer of cottage cheese on the sauce.
Put 1 layer of noodles on that. Continue putting layers of noodles, sauce, cheese until it's all used.
Bake in an oven at 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add apples and pecans last. Let stand 15 minutes before pouring into angel food cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Squeeze juice out of pineapple.
Combine with all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts on wax paper. Serve with Wheat Thins.
Makes 1 large or 2 small.

title: bavarian mint coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well to blend.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 7 minutes and drain.
Combine broccoli with soup, mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Beat egg; add sugar.
Alternate milk and Bisquick.
Fold in grated carrots.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Saute in a little butter onions, chilies and tomato, until lightly browned or onion is tender.
Add cheese and simmer until melted.
Add a drop or two of Tabasco sauce.
If too thick add a little milk.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: baked carrots
directions: Melt butter and saute onion for 3 minutes.
Add shredded carrots.
Put in baking dish.
Mix salt, honey and lemon juice and pour over carrot mixture.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into either graham
cracker of chocolate wafer crust.
Chill.
May be garnished with crushed peanuts or grated chocolate.

title: hot bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon crisp and crumble.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
In crock-pot, place all ingredients. Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 4 hours.
Can be baked in a casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10, if used as a side dish.
Easy to double or triple.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: taylor's turtle brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap caramels and set aside.

title: hamburger beef stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and add onions; cooking until tender.
Stir in soup and 1 soup can of water.
Add salt and pepper.

title: saucy chicken and asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in a greased 9 inch square baking pan.
In a skillet over medium heat brown chicken on both sides in oil. Season with salt and pepper.

title: st.  blanc barbecue shrimp
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a large black pot with cover. Bring to a boil over a hot heat.
Cover and turn off heat.
Test the shrimp every five minutes to see if they are cooked.
Serve in bowl with lots of French bread to sop up liquid.
Serves 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and onion.
Add egg, gradually beat in milk or water.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.
Makes 16 small hush puppies.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat, salt, pepper and onion.
Get bread a little wet; pinch up in mixture.
Mix well.
Brown flour in oil; add tomato juice and boil.
Put some mixture into green pepper, then make the rest of mixture into balls and drop in the juice. After beginning to boil, turn to medium; cook for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix.
Marinate 2 to 3 pound round steak in mixture at least 2 hours.
Slice bell peppers and saute in a little oil.
Remove from pan.
Brown steak.
Boil 1 cup water and dissolve one bouillon cube and pour over steak.
Add bell peppers and simmer until tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put crackers on top (I like cheese crackers).
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: barbecue ribs king style(sauce)
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender; bring sauce to a boil, reduce heat and let simmer about 4 minutes.
Bake ribs or chicken as usual and during the last 10 minutes, baste with sauce.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased baking dish. Bake at 375° until firm and light brown, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with catsup or chill sauce.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine green beans, corn, kidney beans, green pepper and onion rings in bowl; toss to mix.
Add dressing; mix well. Marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: wolverine wash
directions: Shake with ice and strain over ice cubes in an old-fashioned glass rimmed with salt.

title: pretend poached eggs on toast
directions: Place slice of pound cake on a plate.
Put peach half on top, cling side down.
Spread whipped topping around edge of peach covering cake.
Leave bare middle of peach so it looks like a poached egg.
Serve immediately.

title: paradise cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; quarter marshmallows and cut the grapes and cherries in halves.
Combine fruit with sugar; fold in 1/2 cup of whipped cream and nuts.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: luscious banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Stir 1/4 cup of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat. add butter and vanilla.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Drop one vanilla wafer on the bottom of approximately 40 midget foil baking cups.
Put cream cheese mixture on top of wafer.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, put 2 cherries and some juice on top.
Chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut
potatoes	and
carrots
in
chunks.
Combine
all ingredients together in roasting pan with tightly covered lid. Bake in a 250° oven for 8 hours.

title: special k cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a pan and cook on medium-low heat until mixture begins to bubble around the edge of pan.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup of peanut butter.
Pour over 6 cups of Special K.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain and cool in refrigerator.
Add fruit to macaroni and chill.
Cook together sugar, flour, salt, eggs and cup of reserved pineapple juice. Cook until thick.
Cool. Pour over fruit and add Cool Whip. Mix well.
When serving, garnish with maraschino cherry halves. You can make this ahead and freeze.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into round balls.
Handle meat with wet hands.
Place in
greased	pan and brown in oven first one side and then the
other.
Cover
pan and bake until meat is cooked through.

title: vinegar dumplings
directions: Pour over rolls and bake.

title: alex's cut-out cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Gradually stir in flour. Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out dough and have fun.
Bake at 300° about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: hawaiian teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in refrigerator.

title: sweet and spicy fruit kabobs
directions: Thread avocado, pineapple and orange segments alternately onto 6 wooden skewers.
Serve with dressing.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: At Christmas, serve steaming.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy; add sugar and cream again until fluffy.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Sift soda with flour, then add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan or angel food cake pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marcine's mexican wedding cakes(swedish cookies)
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar. Add vanilla and mix well. Gradually add sifted flour and chopped nuts. Refrigerate mixture for at least 2 hours. Roll into small balls about the size of a walnut. Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 350 to 375° for about 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread the crescent rolls on a baking sheet or pizza pan. Bake according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with chopped vegetables.
Slice and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Chop chicken meat into small pieces.
Simmer celery until tender then drain (save).
Mix all ingredients together, save half of noodles for top of casserole. If too dry add some liquid from celery or chicken broth.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and salt all together and set overnight. Rinse and drain the next day.
Mix remaining ingredients in pan. Cook for 30 minutes, stirring a lot.
Pour into hot jars, then seal.

title: jumbo pasta shells
directions: Cook shells according to pkg. instructions.
Brown meats and onions.
Drain.
When shells are done, drain well and stuff with meat mixture.
In a 15 x 10 casserole dish, place just enough sauce to cover bottom.
Place stuffed shells side by side and pour remaining sauce over top.
Cover with the two cheeses & bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Good served with salad and garlic bread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Combine powdered sugar and margarine.
Beat in orange peel and orange juice until well mixed.

title: irene's swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Form into 25 small meat balls. Brown.
Remove from pan and put in casserole dish or roaster. Make a milk gravy with drippings and pour over meat balls.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Add dry jello to cottage cheese; mix well.
Let stand in the refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Fold in Cool Whip to the mixture. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 more hours until stiff.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add to cornmeal mix.
Add 1/2 cheese into mixture.
Use other 1/2 cheese to pour on top.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken and cheese roll-up
directions: Bake chicken ahead of time (I use 3 chicken breasts).
Set aside.
Mix soup, broth and cheese.
Place in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Pinch chicken up.
Place inside crescent rolls. Roll up.
Pour soup and cheese mixture on top of crescent rolls and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(My children's favorite dish.)

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel and cube (1/2-inch cubes) eggplant.
Add salt.
Let drain on paper towels for 1/2 hour, then pat dry.
Empty tomatoes into saucepan.
Mix in egg.
Before heating, add 1 1/2 cups grated cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
Add the eggplant.
Stir in crushed cracker crumbs until you get slightly firm consistency.
Add 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cook 45 minutes. Cover if it starts drying out.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix and hot water; place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle pork chops with pepper and place on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover casserole; combine cream of celery soup and milk, and pour over casserole.
Bake casserole, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: healthy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash potatoes and remove eyes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in frypan.
Brown onion in oleo.
Add rice and brown lightly.
Pour bouillon and consomme over rice.
Add dash of salt if desired.
Pour at once into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain off water.
Add margarine, salt, pepper, sour cream and 2 cups of cornbread crumbs or stuffing.
Butter casserole dish and line bottom with remaining 2 cups of cornbread crumbs or stuffing.
Pour squash mixture into dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Add cheese; bake until cheese is melted.

title: easy lemon torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then cool.

title: igloo
directions: Melt margarine with sugar, nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Put layer of cookies with one teaspoon of mix on each cookie.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Best made two or three days before serving.

title: dora's biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: white frosting
directions: Frosts 2 (9-inch) layer cake, 9 x 13-inch layer or large tube cake.

title: homemade hot cocoa mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Store in tightly covered container.
For a single serving, combine 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup boiling water in cup and stir to blend.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits and salt in boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cut 1 roll of garlic cheese and 1 stick of butter.
Melt cheese and butter.
Beat 2 eggs; heat slightly.
Add cup of milk.
Add all ingredients to grit mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble 5 or 6 Ritz crackers (or Cheddar cheese crackers) and cover the mixture with crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Great with fish or tuna salad.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Put cake mix, pudding mix, fruit cocktail (juice and all), 1 cup of the coconut, eggs, and oil into mixing bowl and beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Combine the brown sugar and chopped nuts in a separate bowl.
Pour cake batter into a greased & floured 9 X 13 cake pan and sprinkle with nut/sugar mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until cake springs back when touched and pulls away from the pan.
Do not under bake.
Bring margarine, white sugar and evaporated milk to a boil in a medium pan, simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the remaining 1 1/2 cups coconut and spoon over the cake that has cooled for 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fudge
directions: Mix in 2-quart saucepan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil ( mixture will be bubbling all over).
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Take off heat. Stir in 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: spanish gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Use to taste pepper, garlic salt, seasoned salt, etc.
Mix and let stand at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and pie cherries.
Add pineapple and nuts. Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve as salad.

title: cheese green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain bacon and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons.

Cook beans as directed. Add onion to the reserved 1/4 cup bacon drippings in skillet. Cook on medium-high heat for 5 minutes, then add drained mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes more. Add beans, bacon (except the 2 tablespoons) and pepper to the onion and mushrooms.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.
Microwave Cheez Whiz. Pour over green bean mixture.
Sprinkle the 2 tablespoons bacon on top.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas ribbon jello
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water and 1 1/2 cups cold water to the lime jello; let set.
Add 1 cup boiling water to the lemon jello.
Beat in the cream cheese.
Cool.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and whipping cream.
Pour over green mixture; let set.
Add 2 cups boiling water and 1 1/2 cups cold water to the red jello.
Cool and pour over all.
Let set.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs and buttermilk in large bowl, stirring until blended.
Stir in butter and vanilla and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Cool on wire rack.

title: fruit bars
directions: Chop fine pineapple, cherries and dates.
Line pan with heavy brown paper.
Grease well.
Bake at 275° for approximately 45 minutes.
Let set out of oven for 15 minutes.
Remove paper.
Cut and roll in xxxx sugar when cool.

title: trawler crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Captain's wafers or any crackers.
For a little extra flavor, add more horseradish.

title: turkey sandwich delight
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Place toast on foil.
Spread broccoli on top of toast.
Lay turkey on top of broccoli.
Melt half of the grated cheese in milk; pour over turkey.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Broil until cheese has melted and starts to brown.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add the mixed vegetables and cream of mushroom soup. Top with Tater Tots and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon, egg and cheese sandwich
directions: Fry bacon.
Scramble two eggs.
Butter bread and cook with cheese like grilled cheese sandwich.
Pull bread apart and put eggs in.
Break up bacon and put on top of eggs.
Put bread back together and eat.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook onion, pepper and carrots in margarine in a 3-quart saucepan for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and mix well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add broth and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese has melted.
Add milk.
Season and bring just to boiling, but do not boil.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let set for several hours or overnight. (Very good.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Peanut
butter
and cream cheese should be room temperature. Mix
these
two ingredients first and add powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: curried cheese pate
directions: Beat together thoroughly the cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, curry powder and salt.
Spread on a serving platter, shaping a layer about 1/2-inch thick.
Chill until firm.

title: honey butter scones
directions: In mixing bowl, combine honey, butter and salt.
Mix until soft and smooth.
Add 1 cup very hot tap water and stir until butter mixture has melted.
In a glass bowl, mix yeast, sugar and 1/4 cup very warm water (if using thermometer, water should be about 110°).
Mix and set aside until yeast mixture has doubled in size.
Add 1 cup of flour to butter mixture; stir until smooth. Slowly stir in yeast mixture.
Add the remaining flour until stiff and elastic like.
Knead for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut into 6 to 8 equal parts.
Will rolling pin, roll to about 1/8-inch thick.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Mash and add egg yolks.
Crumble crackers; add butter.
Add to squash mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Beat egg whites and stir in.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: jean's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and blend well. Add eggs and blend.
