Fold in sour cream and flavoring.
Fold gently until no sour cream shows.

title: rich brown beef stew
directions: Put meat and flour in a paper bag; shake until all pieces of meat are coated with flour.
Brown meat in fat in heavy skillet with any extra flour that is in bag.
Add water and seasonings. Cover tightly and simmer for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue cooking 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix together all at once.
Grill as pancakes.

title: orange picnic cake
directions: Heat the orange juice to boiling and pour over the oats.
Set aside.
Cream the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add the vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.

Blend into creamed mixture alternately with the juice and oats, beginning and ending with the flour mixture. Fold in the walnut pieces and orange rind. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes in an oblong cake pan.
Cool, spread on frosting and broil for 1 minute.

title: ice cream cake
directions: If you can't find Swiss chocolate, use your favorite chocolate.

title: summer bean salad
directions: For dressing, whisk together oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except lettuce leaves.
Toss with dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chocolate kiss pie
directions: Melt Kisses in microwave; let cool for a little while.
Mix with Cool Whip and put in graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken dumpling soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Take chicken out of broth; shred meat (discarding skin and bones) and place meat back in broth.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour entire batter the hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: chocolate crispies
directions: Melt almond bark squares in a double boiler.
Add salted peanuts without red skins.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Ready to eat.

title: buttercream eggs
directions: New England housewives slice ripe Pumpkins, dice them and fill a pot to 2 or 3 gallons and stew gently a whole day.
Stewed enough they look like bak'd Apples; this they Dish, add Butter, Vinegar and Spices, and serve to be eaten with Fish or Flesh.
It provokes (sic) and is very windy.

title: cinnamon applesauce bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream oleo and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add oatmeal mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon. bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: peggy's vodka chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil and butter; remove from pan.
Add vodka and bring to boil.
Turn down heat; add tomatoes, cream and basil. Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and cook until chicken is done (4 to 5 minutes).
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix sauce, dressing and soup mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in uncovered 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish until chicken is tender.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add sugar; stir.
Add milk gradually.
Cook and stir until it comes to a gentle boil. Simmer and stir for a minute or two, or until thick and creamy.

title: porcupine balls
directions: In saucepan, put dates, beaten egg, sugar and butter.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Stir.
Mix into small balls and roll in flaked coconut.

title: seafood batter
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Combine egg, flour and salt.
Add beer to mixture.
Drop fish or seafood into batter and drop in hot oil.

title: sister-in-laws
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond flavoring.

title: shirley's favorite rice - "sour creamed"
directions: To cooked rice, add chilies, cheese and sour cream (half of the cheese).
Spoon into buttered dish.
Sprinkle the other half of the cheese on top.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: deviled (angel) eggs
directions: Add mustard, mayonnaise, sugar and salt to mashed yolks.
Mix all together; fill whites with mix.
Sprinkle top of eggs with paprika.

title: reelfoot lake earthquake cake
directions: Mix together coconut and chopped nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix.
Mix as directed.
Mix and drop on top of cake mix using a teaspoon cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spring pea and mint spread(low-fat; use in place of guacamole)
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a food processor until blended (but not pureed).
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Spread on party bread.
Great accompaniment to cheese and crackers.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position.
Heat oven to 425°.
Roll out half of the dough on a lightly floured surface with a lightly floured rolling pin to a 12-inch circle.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with dough.
Mix brown sugar, flour and spices in a large bowl. Add apples and lemon juice; toss gently to mix and coat.
Spread in pie plate, mounding apples in center.
Scrape any juices in bowl over apples.

title: mussel timbale(serves 4)
directions: Steam open mussels with water, shallots and herbs.
Remove mussels from shells.
Strain broth and boil down until it measures 1 cup.
Melt butter in a double boiler over hot water.
Add flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in broth and heat sauce until it thickens.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir eggs into cooled sauce.
Fold in mussels and pour into a large buttered casserole dish.
Place in a pan of hot water and bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test by inserting a knife into the center, it should come out uncoated.
Allow a few minutes to set before serving.
If desired, serve with hot mushroom sauce.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp.
Melt butter in a large skillet and saute onion and green pepper.
Stir in garlic; remove from heat and blend in flour.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes. Add water, then stir in shrimp and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick kahlua tiramisu
directions: Place cake slices in shallow dessert dishes.
Moisten with coffee.
Top each with 1 scoop of ice cream.
Pour the Kahlua over the ice cream.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate or cocoa.
Serve immediately.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix well,
roll
out and cut with cookie cutter or bake in muffin pans.
Extra fluffy.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Line bowl with thin layer of wafers.
Mix pudding with milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over wafers.
Add remaining wafers and rest of pudding.
Smooth on strawberry glaze and top with strawberries that have been cut into halves.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in deep pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage ratatouille
directions: In a skillet, heat sausages and water to boiling.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking, turning sausages, until browned (about 10 minutes).
Remove sausages; drain and slice.
Add oil to drippings in pan; saute green peppers, eggplant and onions until browned.
Return sausages to skillet.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, zucchini, sugar, salt and thyme.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in beans; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma grant's salad dressing
directions: Cut bacon in tiny pieces and fry out in saucepan; set aside half of the fried bacon.
Beat the eggs; add the salt, sugar, vinegar and water.
Beat well and add to the bacon and the bacon fat in saucepan.
Heat slowly, beating constantly until the mixture thickens.
Remove from the fire and add the cream.
Pour this over a head of lettuce, garden lettuce.
Garnish with additional bacon and some hard-boiled eggs.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In an ungreased 9-inch pan, stir together the first 8 ingredients.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour the hot water over all.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes and serve with ice cream.
This bakes up to be cake on top and hot fudge sauce on the bottom.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Dissolve baking soda in milk and stir in bananas.
Add this to butter and sugar mixture and mix in flour, which has been sifted with baking powder.
Fold in nuts and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese, crabmeat, onion, milk, horseradish and salt, mixing well until blended.
Stir in almonds.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine oat bran, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
Lightly beat egg whites with fork, then stir in milk, oil and orange zest.
Pour into flour mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in dates and nuts.
Fill 12 paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° until done, about 20 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: spinach salad with prosciutto dressing
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add prosciutto and garlic; saute 3 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and sugar; simmer 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl and cool completely.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: quick banana cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and baking soda and beat as directed on cake mix box. Fold in bananas and walnuts. Pour into a floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven saute onion and pepper in oleo for 3 minutes. Add the meat and brown, breaking up with spoon as it cooks.
Add salt, black pepper and sugar.
Stir in the tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In large pan, crumble corn bread to coarse pieces. Drain beans; spread over corn bread. Spread tomatoes, pepper, onion and pickles over corn bread. Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice. Blend well. Pour over salad. Refrigerate 24 hours. Keeps well for several days.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks, then add sugar.
Mix well. Fold in crushed crackers and pecans.
Spread in 7 x 11-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes, until light brown.
Cool.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Combine into a mealy mixture.
Roll into balls.
Melt wax and then chocolate chips in wax.
Place in a double boiler and dip peanut butter balls.
Place on aluminum foil and cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Shred cheeses in a large bowl; mix well.
Cook meat in large skillet or pan until pink is cooked out; drain.l
In another skillet, saute onions in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add to beef, 1/2 of cheeses, olives, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder and salt; stir all together until all cheese has been melted.
Put a rounded tablespoonful or a little more, depending on tortilla size, of meat mixture into the tortilla.
Roll it up in baking dish.
Roll up next one by it, and so on.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken breast; you can use 1 whole chicken.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together with chicken breast.
Place in dish.
Top with crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries, eggs and oil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool. Makes 2 loaves.

title: kahlua-orange fudge cake
directions: Grease	and
flour
a
10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
In a large mixer
bowl,
beat	all
ingredients
(except chocolate chips)
on low speed, until blended.
Beat on medium speed for 4
minutes. Stir in chocolate pieces.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool
on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook celery and onion together in a little water.
Pour off water. Mix chicken, rice, onion, celery and cream of chicken soup. Add mayonnaise last.

title: mrs. ?'s cookies
directions: *Use a food processor or a blender to grind regular oats into a powder.

title: johnita's rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Let cool.
Add yeast, dissolved in warm water.
Add flour; don't get dough too stiff.
Turn dough into greased bowl; grease top of dough, then cover with cloth.
Let rise at least 2 hours.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll out dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds with a small juice glass or donut hole cutter.
Melt stick of butter in a small bowl.
Dip rolls in butter.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased) and let rise, uncovered, 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen small rolls.

title: chess cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Drain beans; combine in a large bowl with green pepper and onion.
Make dressing:
in a small saucepan combine the sugar, vinegar, oil, and seasonings.
Bring to a boil over medium hear to melt the sugar.
Pour dressing over the beans and toss to mix all together. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Arrange ingredients in layers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream Shortening, add sugar, applesauce, beaten egg.
Sift a little flour over raisin and nuts.
Sift remaining flour will seasonings and fold into applesauce mixture. Blend in soda and water.
Then fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 in square pan at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Chill.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; cut.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and pineapple.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add baby food and cream cheese, stirring until smooth. Add 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip (thawed).

title: rolls(40% bran flake cereal)
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling water over Crisco.
Add sugar, salt and bran.
Dissolve yeast in one cup lukewarm water.
Add yeast mixture to bran mixture.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and mix until large ball forms.
Place dough in large greased bowl and let rise 2 hours or until doubled in size.
Punch down.
At this point, you can refrigerate or roll out and make into rolls.
Let rise (approximately 1 hour) and bake in preheated oven at 425° or until browned.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Batter rises as it cooks and falls down when done.
Freezes well.

title: beef or deer jerky
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Layer meat between foil and roll with a rolling pin until 1/8 thick.
Remove from foil and place directly onto own racks.

title: hug and kisses butter cookies
directions: In a small cup, stir egg yolk and vanilla together.
In a food processor, place flour, sugar and salt.
Process 10 seconds.
Add butter; process until mixture resembles coarse meal, 20 to 30 seconds.
Add yolk with machine running through the feed tube and process 5 seconds; scrape the bowl, then process until the liquid is evenly absorbed, about 10 seconds.
Remove dough to a work surface.
Press dough together until it forms a ball.
Divide dough in half and shape into 2 thick disks.
Wrap each in plastic wrap. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 350°.

Lightly butter several cookie sheets. Remove dough from refrigerator and allow it to soften slightly. Place each piece of dough between 2 new pieces wrap or waxed paper. Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Remove top wax paper.
Cut any desired shape.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and slice squash.
Cook until tender, 20 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sour cream, soup, diced chicken and stuffing crumbs. Mix well.
In a saucepan, melt butter and
simmer seasoning (included in stuffing mix) with water for 5 minutes.
Pour into soup mixture and gently fold in the squash.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: magic mushrooms
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and Cavender's Greek seasoning.
Shake well and pour over mushrooms, onions and cheese when ready to serve.

title: mashed red potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skin until well done. Drain and mash. Saut onion and butter in microwave. Layer potatoes, onion, sour cream and cheese. Save some cheese for top.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: In large mixing
bowl
cream together butter and sugar. Blend in syrup, vanilla and eggs; beating well after each one. Sift into mixture
dry
ingredients.
Pour
into
greased
and floured pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Cook sugar, water and cinnamon together for about 5 minutes. Pour over nuts in buttered pan. Cool and break apart.

title: artichoke-mushroom casserole
directions: Put artichokes in casserole dish.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 10 minutes; drain (save butter in pan).
Add mushrooms to artichokes.
Put sour cream in pan with butter; blend well.
Add seasonings and parsley; pour over artichokes and mushrooms.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Note:
These ingredients may be minced in blender.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix well.
It is ready to serve.
The salad will keep well in the refrigerator for about 1 week.

title: broccoli-corn salad
directions: Arrange broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 5 to 6 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Let cool. Combine broccoli, corn and pimiento in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a small bowl; stir well with a wire whisk.
Pour vinegar mixture over broccoli mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill.

title: pineapple-poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine gelatin and pineapple juice in saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly 2 to 3 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve over fruit salads.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl mix together first six (6) ingredients.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown meat mixture.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Drain and add sour cream and cream cheese.
Arrange meat and noodle mixture in a large greased oblong pan.
Alternate layers ending with meat mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix cake
mix,
eggs, pecans and softened oleo.
Mix together and
press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves. When syrup boils, blend in butter. Stir frequently after mixture reaches 230°. Add nuts when temperature reaches 280° and stir constantly until temperature reaches 305°. Remove from heat. Quickly stir in soda. Pour onto 2 cookie sheets or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch pans. Loosen from pans as soon as possible. Break in pieces.

title: wiener casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a buttered 1-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: french chicken
directions: Cook artichoke hearts according to the directions on the package.
Drain well.
In a heavy skillet, brown the chicken in the shortening.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the artichokes.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Add the artichokes and heat.
Serve with rice.
Served with a green salad and a fruit dessert, this makes a very tasty, easy dinner which has a "party" taste.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken thoroughly.
For best results, use Corning Ware dish or dish with tight fitting lid.
Place chicken in container.
Add salt, pepper and seasoning salt.
Slice onion and spread over meat.
Slice green pepper and spread over meat. Add butter (do not have to melt.
Add barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour.
Can be assembled several days in advance.
A good side dish to accompany the holiday bird.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into ball.
Cover with crushed nuts, if desired.
Chill.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain and cool. Peel potatoes; cut into cubes and set aside.
Combine relish, onion, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper in a large salad bowl, stirring well.
Fold in sour cream and potatoes, celery and eggs. Toss gently; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: baked ham with apples
directions: Mix mustard, pepper and brown sugar.
Rub over ham slice. Place in a baking dish.
Core apples.
Cut them in 1/2-inch slices.
Cover the ham thickly with the apples.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Cover the bottom of the pan with water.
Cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and let top brown.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli in small flowerets.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over broccoli; cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Baste from time to time.
Drain and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In a large bowl, put cooked, drained pasta, flaked corned beef, onion and half of bread crumbs.
Toss together.
Add cubed cheese and mix with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Empty can of soup into bowl.
Mix with a little water or milk to make smooth.
Pour over pasta.
Melt butter in pan and add rest of bread crumbs.
Cook on low until toasted.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well with 1 teaspoon grated onion.
Mix well and chill. Form 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: marge's fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture. Brown in hot grease (Crisco), turning constantly until evenly browned.
Turn down to low heat and put lid on and simmer until tender.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix in broth and milk.
Stir until thick.
Add chicken.
Serve on biscuits.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and oil.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture, mixing after each addition.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful into confectioners sugar, coating lightly.
Shape into balls. Place on greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine butter and cocoa and stir into egg mixture.
Add pecans and coconut, mixing well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until set.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients real well.
Add beef and mix. (I use food processor.)

title: scotch crispies
directions: In bottom part of double boiler, bring water to boiling point, then turn heat to low.
Melt morsels and peanut butter over hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in cornflakes until well coated. Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: outback chili
directions: Combine beef, garlic, and onion in a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cook and stir until beef is brown.
Drain fat; add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer for at least 1 hour, uncovered.

title: casserole for 10
directions: Cook and drain rice.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix by hand flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt together.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add nuts, if desired.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Add cream cheese to Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve cream cheese.
Mix in the other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: muffin cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix first 6 ingredients together. For each muffin, press 1/2 of a biscuit in a mini muffin tin. Add heaping teaspoon of filling. Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes. Makes 40-48.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all in blender and blend at medium speed.
Pour in greased pie pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: classic swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving portions.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in medium size bowl.
Roll cut steaks in flour mixture, coating both sides.
Melt shortening or butter in hot skillet. Brown meat on both sides but do not cook.
Place browned meat in crock-pot.
Add tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Cook on low for 6 to 12 hours or on high for up to 6 hours.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Proof yeast. Combine dry ingredients in food processor and pulse. Add butter and process until mealy. Combine wet ingredients and process until mealy. Combine wet ingredients. Add to processor and pulse until ball forms. Refrigerate overnight. Punch down and divide in 1/2. Pat into 12-inch circle and cut into 12 wedges. Roll into crescents. Place on greased sheet and brush with melted butter. Repeat with other half. Let rise 1 hour. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Makes 24 rolls.

title: pasta with carbonara sauce
directions: Eggs, margarine and cream must be room temperature. Beat together eggs and cream until blended. Cook pasta; drain well. Turn into a preheated (250°) ovenproof dish. Toss in margarine and pepperoni; mix well. Pour egg mixture over; toss well. Add cheese and parsley. Toss again. Mixture will continue to cook in hot dish. Do not bake.

title: curried fruit
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Drain and dry fruit.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix butter with sugar and curry powder and spread over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: stroganoff burgers
directions: Brown beef and bacon.
Add onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain off fat.
Blend flour and seasonings into meat. Stir in soup and cook slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: easy thousand island dressing
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients; blend well. Cover and chill.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Cook ground turkey, onion, garlic, salt and basil in skillet. Spread cottage cheese over meat mixture.
Lay 6 lasagna noodles (not cooked) over cottage cheese.
Add the tomatoes.
Cover and cook 35 minutes over low heat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well. Pour into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix brown sugar, margarine, flour and pecans until crumbly. Cover sweet potato mixture with this. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: cold beef with mustard horseradish sauce(prep time:  15 minutes.)
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper. Whisk in the oil until emulsified. Whisk in the scallions, watercress and mayonnaise. Arrange the beef on a platter and serve it with mustard sauce.

title: happy birthday cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, Crisco, salt and 3/4 cup milk. Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder, 1/2 cup milk, eggs and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana split pie
directions: Make pudding according to box directions.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice bananas and spread evenly on top of pudding.
Mix whipped topping, strawberries, and pineapple. Spread evenly over bananas.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Slice and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: savory hot turkey sandwiches
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook carrots, celery and onion with poultry seasoning until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in gravy.
Heat to boiling.
Add turkey slices.
Heat through.
Serve on bread, waffles or biscuits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled pineapple
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Measure 2/3 cup and pour into saucepan.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour at once over pineapple chunks.
Ladle into gift jar.
Arrange cinnamon stick and cherry in jar.
Fill to overflowing with liquid.
Cover and cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.
Keep refrigerated.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Coat beef steak pieces with flour; pound into beef.
Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Push beef to side.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender; drain.
Add enough water to reserved potato liquid to measure 1 cup.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper flakes, instant bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper.
Pour on beef and onion.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Rinse frozen beans under running water to separate. Add potatoes, beans and pimento to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender.

title: tortoni ice cream
directions: Combine in mixer; mix until firm.
Put in cupcake liners and freeze until solid.
Remove from liner wrap in plastic wrap or baggies and put back in freezer until ready to serve.

title: cheese ball dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add pineapple gradually.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pour hash browns in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan. Place meat on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat. Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt; beat well.
Pour over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Serves 8 to 10.
Can do ahead and let sit overnight.

title: gingerbread scones
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Combine molasses and milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring first until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.

title: apple brownies
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Then add rest of dry ingredients. Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar over cranberries.
Fold in Cool Whip. Combine cranberries, pineapple and bananas.
Put 1/2 cup sugar over the fruit and fold in the Cool Whip.
Place cupcake liners in muffin tins and freeze.
Makes 12.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add salt, pepper and flour, stirring until blended.
Add sour cream and cook until thick, stirring often.
Cook green beans as directed; drain well and add sour cream mixture.
Stir well until beans are covered.
Spread in a shallow baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tracy's fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dip your favorite fruit. Tastes great with apples, bananas, oranges and grapes.
Enjoy.

title: ruth ann's pudding dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: holiday soup
directions: Make chicken soup with celery, onion, carrots, chicken, salt, pepper and parsley.
After soup is done, debone chicken. Remove fat and skin.
Cut into small pieces. Add to soup.
Add meatballs and simmer for 10 minutes, then add cooked escarole.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Serve topped with grated cheese.
Delicious!

title: peppermint taffy(by kids)
directions: Grease baking pans with some butter.
Heat all ingredients except the peppermint extract and food color just to boiling in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook without stirring to 256° on candy thermometer or until a small amount of the mixture dropped into glass of very cold water forms a ball, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 tablespoon extract.
Pour half the mixture into one of the buttered pans. Stir 8 to 10 drops color into remaining mixture, then pour into other buttered pan.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan. Combine flour, cocoa and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar in large bowl until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla. Mix. Beat in flour mixture. Reserve 3/4 cup batter. Spread rest of batter in pan. Sprinkle nuts and white chips over batter. Drizzle caramel. Beat remaining egg batter and leftover batter in bowl until light in color. Stir in chocolate chips. Spread over caramel. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Wash and drain berries.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add the dry Jell-O; mix good and cool.
Add berries to mixture; pour into a pie shell.
Cool several hours.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: goblin guzzler for kids
directions: You will need four 10-ounce glasses.

title: inside-outside ravioli
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Cook spinach.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste and pepper into mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach with macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and salad oil.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat sugar and peanut butter until smooth; fold in marshmallow.
Blend well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned on bottom, about 8 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with cinnamon or cocoa if desired.

title: teriyaki steak bites
directions: Combine soy sauce, spices, sugar and wine to make marinade. Marinate meat at least 1 hour.
Drain meat.
Reserve liquid.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in medium skillet. Brown meat cubes quickly on all sides.
Place meat in chafing dish.
Pour sauce over. Stir occasionally.
If you like, add pineapple chunks to chafing dish.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender at high speed for 1 minute, stopping to stir down once.
Bake on greased griddle, using 1/4 cup for each pancake.

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine sour cream and soda.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; gradually add flour mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon 2/3 of batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Top with 1/2 of the nut mixture.
Add remaining batter and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is ready.

title: peppercorn sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add shallots and saute until golden.
Add brandy and bring to a boil. Add stock and boil until mixture is reduced to 1 cup, about 5 minutes.
Add cream and peppercorns; cook over medium heat until reduced to sauce consistency, about 5 minutes.
Taste and season with additional crushed peppercorns and salt, if necessary.
(Can be prepared one day ahead.
Cover and chill.
Bring to a simmer before using.)
Serve over your favorite cut of beef.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together!
Put in a glass jar or sealed container.
Put 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water!

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form balls the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix these dressing ingredients and add to your usual potato salad contents. Make as many times as you need to cover your potatoes.

title: teriyaki
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Marinate beef strips at least 2 hours.
Use thin slices 1 inch wide, cut against the grain. Thread on bamboo skewers.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Good for chicken, too.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and congeal.

title: apricot kugel
directions: Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated italian salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix according to package directions. Mix vegetables and shrimp together.
Pour dressing over the shrimp and vegetables.
Marinate for twenty-four hours.

title: peanut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook for 2 minutes; sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Then add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in soup pot.
Add water, add diced vegetables (except canned ones), ketchup, tomato juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer slowly 3/4 hour.
Add canned vegetables and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour onto large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach madaline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain spinach and save liquid.
Melt butter in pan and add flour, stirring until completely blended but not browned.
Add onion and cook.
Add milk and liquid from spinach slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and rest of seasonings.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake until warm.
Freezes well.

title: pork chop casserole #1
directions: Salt and pepper and brown chops.
Pour rice along with soup, consomme and mushrooms.
Stir together.
Lay chops on top, adding margarine to top of chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine butter, garlic, mustard and Worcestershire.
Place small amount of cheese in center of each breast.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Dip in butter mixture, then crumb mix.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Slow cook for 1 to 2 hours.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Soak soft bread crumbs in milk.
Mix in ground beef, minced onions, salt, egg and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Shape into loaf in lightly greased, shallow baking dish.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix together the cornmeal, salt and sugar.
Scald these ingredients in
the
boiling
water.
Add
the
butter
to the mixture.
Mix the eggs and milk and stir all together and then add baking
powder; stir to get an even mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium-size bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in bowl.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: bavarian custard
directions: In bowl, mix instant pudding with whisk with milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add sour cream and yogurt.
Whisk again.
Cover and refrigerate two hours before serving.
Spoon into dishes and top with choice of fruit.

title: rich fudge
directions: Beat until creamy.
Pour into pan. Cook at 350° until fudge tests done.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken into mixture of melted butter, hot pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package of Hidden Valley Ranch.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: the miller's hot chili
directions: Saute onions and cayenne peppers in 1 teaspoon of vegetable oil until onions are tender.
Add meat and brown.
Crush tomatoes and add to meat mixture in large pot.
Add rest of ingredients, except tomato juice, and mix thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato juice.
Cook on medium/low heat for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low setting for another hour. Stir occasionally.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, pour off grease.
Blend in gravy mix, garlic salt, water and rice.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in thawed peas and chestnuts, cut up. Continue to simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in onions.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: ground turkey spaghetti
directions: Using about 1 tablespoon of garlic with ground turkey; form meatballs and place in a 13 x 18-inch pan.
Bake meatballs until done in 300° oven.
Remove from heat and make sauce.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Then add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Put oatmeal in a blender until it turns to powder.
Mix with flour, then add salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "hearty" lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic in oil until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper.
Place carrots and celery in sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
Remove and discard carrots and celery.

title: a luscious salad
directions: Mix into mixture and let set in refrigerator at least overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf with party crackers.
Makes fifteen generous servings.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir well; pour out on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread well. When cool, break into chunks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut up vegetables real small or dice.
Toss spaghetti with Italian dressing and Salad Supreme seasoning.
Cut spaghetti in small segments.
Add cut up raw vegetables.
Toss.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Better if made the day before.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients and make 3 holes.
Then add rest of ingredients and pour 1 cup of water over ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and add vanilla pudding and milk.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, well drained.
Spread mixture over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 12 hours or more.
Cut in squares and top each square with a cherry.

title: skinless boneless chicken tenders
directions: Pour over chicken and refrigerate 1/2 to 1 hour.
Grill or broil chicken.
Warm the sauce and put chicken in it; serve.

title: bird's nest
directions: Bring peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla to a boil.
Stir into cereal and coconut.
Let cool.
Shape into bird's nests and fill with jelly bean eggs.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine the vegetables, salt and sugar and cook until mixture begins to thicken, then add the vinegar and spices in a bag.
Cook until mixture becomes a thick sauce.
Pour into hot jars and seal immediately.
Drain juice from vegetables before adding vinegar. This will shorten the cooking time.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add 7-Up and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add lemon oil or extract.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: picnic cake
directions: Arrange peaches and juice evenly on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle coconut and walnuts evenly over cake mix.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble cheese and blend all ingredients together.
Add buttermilk to thin.
Refrigerate for at least one day.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sugar-free gingerbread cookies
directions: Beat margarine, butter, egg and vanilla until fluffy. Stir together flour, baking powder, ginger and pumpkin pie spice (or in place of pumpkin pie spice, use a pinch of each: ground cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, clove). Add to egg mixture and mix well (batter will be stiff). Roll out thinly and cut into 2-inch rounds with an inverted glass, or cut into shapes with a decorative cookie cutter. Arrange cookies 1-inch apart on baking tray sprayed with baking spray. Bake in a preheated 375° oven 6 or 7 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzels.

title: ground meat and beans
directions: Brown meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all other ingredients in and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut
sweet potatoes in pieces and arrange in 8 or 9-inch Pyrex
dish.
Cut butter in pieces and dot potatoes. Drizzle syrup over potatoes and top with cereal.
Bake on High for 4 minutes.	Turn
dish
and bake for 4 more minutes.
Turn dish and bake for 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix together ground chuck, 3 eggs, Italian bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
In a large Dutch oven, put 1/4 cup oil.
Chop finely 1 onion and 2 buttons of garlic.
Saute onions until soft.
Add garlic, finely chopped.
Put in tomato paste, tomatoes (crushed), Italian spices plus oregano, salt and pepper.
Let simmer while you brown your meat balls.
When browned, add to tomato mixture.
Let simmer 3 hours at least.
Add a can of water to each paste can and about 1/3 tomato can.
Keep low heat.
Stir often.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Form mixture into several patties.
Add 2 tablespoons oil in frying pan and heat to 325°.
Brown patties on each side (approximately 3 minutes each side).

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
(This recipe may be doubled.
Bake 2 pies, freeze one for later use.)

title: egg souffle
directions: Butter a large casserole and make three layers each as follows:
1 cup bread crumbs, 1 cup cubed ham and 1 cup cheese. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon butter and repeat.
Blend eggs, milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over casserole mixture of bread, ham and cheese.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve with tossed green salad, roll and dessert.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Mix together; pour in greased skillet and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: green tomatoes, fried
directions: Rinse, trim and cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices. Beat egg with milk, salt and pepper. In another bowl, combine flour, cracker crumbs and a dash of salt. Dip tomato slices in the egg mixture, then in the flour mixture. Heat oil to 350° in a heavy skillet and gently cook tomato slices about 3 minutes on each side. Drain excess fat on a paper towel. Serves 6.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add potatoes, beaten eggs and salt.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to mixture.
Beat well and add to flour, a little at a time, until all is used.
Mix thoroughly and let stand until dough has doubled in size.
Punch down, cover and place in refrigerator.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix sugar, water and cloves.
Simmer 20 minutes on low heat. Add tea, orange juice and lemon juice.
Add water, straining out cloves.
Add pineapple juice last.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in ovenproof serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: deep dish old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° until a silver knife comes out clean.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook slow (3 to 3 1/2 hours or until as thick as you want it). Put in jars.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into mold and refrigerate.
When firm, spread sour cream on firm jello and top with remaining jello mixture.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased iron skillet and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edge of pudding is crusty.

title: ice cream for 4 quart freezer
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream yolks with sugar in mixer.
Add milk, about 2 cups.
Beat whites and add.
Whip cream and add.
If fruit is desired, sweeten to taste and add.
Pour in freezer and add enough milk to fill freezer to fill line.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Peaches, strawberries or bananas are delicious.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Break up bread and add other ingredients.
(Use enough broth to make mixture very moist, even soggy.)
Pour into baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease entire pan with butter.
(Use an angel food cake pan.) Cover bottom of pan with nuts and raisins.
(Use amount of nuts and raisins to your liking.)
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Add Riches frozen rolls.
(Layer them all around evenly.)
Sprinkle the vanilla pudding all around.
(Do not cook the pudding.) Sprinkle the brown sugar all around.
(Use amount to your liking.) Spread 1/4 stick of melted butter all around.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Heat bourbon, butter and Italian dressing.
Cool.
Lay shrimp in shallow pan.
Poke small holes with fork in one side of shrimp shell (5 or 6).
Pour marinade over shrimp.
Let soak a few hours, letting marinade seep into shells.
Grill for 1 minute on each side.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Mix peas, cauliflower, water chestnuts, broccoli and celery. Spread in a layer in a small pan.
Mix dressing mix, mayonnaise and sour cream; pour over the vegetable mix.
May add bacon bits to the top.

title: norwegian gluige(holiday after-dinner drink served in cordial glasses)
directions: Combine wine and spices in large soup pot.
Heat on stove. Light wine with match.
Sprinkle sugar over flames.
Cover to kill flames.
Add rye.
Cool and bottle.
Prepare at least one month before Christmas.

title: low-fat breakfast
directions: Put applesauce in bowl.
Crumble graham crackers on top.
Put a pat of low-fat margarine on top; heat in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: easy spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil with onions, garlic, Italian seasoning and bay leaves.
When done, remove from heat, remove and discard bay leaves.
Let cool while cooking spaghetti.
Drain spaghetti, add to beef mixture along with evaporated milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan which has been greased or sprayed with nonstick spray. Top with Velveeta.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken, rice & broccoli casserole
directions: Mix margarine, flour salt & pepper in saucepan.
Add milk and heat.
When thick, add remaining ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: crab meat appetizer pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Spread on flat pizza pie pan. Cover mixture with chili sauce. Top with crumbled crab meat.
Top with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
Looks very festive for Christmas.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and let stand for 5 minutes.
Let stand 24 hours before attempting to pick up newsprint.
Store in small plastic Easter eggs.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, then 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until sauce thickens.

title: williamsburg chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except almonds.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix everything, except pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: corn custard
directions: Put all ingredients into blender except half of the corn. Cover and blend until smooth.
Put the remainder of the corn in the bottom of a greased baking dish (9 x 12-inch or similar). Pour your mixture over the top of the corn and place this pan into another pan filled with hot water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.
(Careful, it burns easy!)

title: not edible brown bread dough
directions: Dissolve salt in water.
Add flour and oil.
Knead to mix dough.
May be baked at 300°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix and pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Cut around edges and drizzle topping over bread.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pizza fruit pie
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green pepper relish
directions: Well drain the peppers; add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and then cool slowly for 5 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell and a few drops of food coloring.
Stir in completely.
Pour in jars and add paraffin wax to seal.
Can be stored in cupboard for a year.
Serve on crackers with cream cheese as an appetizer.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: In a large bowl or deep dish, place by layer, each of the following ingredients:
lettuce, frozen peas, frozen vegetables, sliced chicken strips and mayonnaise.
Cover, chill for 2 to 3 hours, then ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: layered salad
directions: In a gallon container with tight fitting lid (ice cream tub is perfect), place torn lettuce. Sprinkle green onions, celery and water chestnuts (all chopped) on top. Add layer of peas and do not toss. Spread mayo on top and sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Top with tomatoes and egg slices. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 24 hours. Toss and serve.

title: fettucini
directions: In large saucepan, stir soup until smooth; blend in milk and cheese on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water, drain.
Place servings on plate, top with fettucini sauce and enjoy.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to other mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients
together
in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Pour
in
oil, pumpkin and water.
Blend well with an electric mixer.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a
time, beating after each. Pour into
2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool loaves on a wire rack.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: For variety, use different cheeses (Swiss, etc.).

title: milk jello
directions: Mix gelatine with 1/4 cup water.
In separate bowl, mix remainder of
ingredients
(except	for
milk).
Add milk when jello starts
to cool.
Refrigerate for approximately 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, then add another layer, if desired.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Blanch in boiling water for 2 minutes the broccoli and carrots.
Drain.

title: tomatoes with basil
directions: Layer tomato slices in ceramic or glass serving dish.
In small bowl, whisk together basil, red wine vinegar, salt and pepper.
Whisk in olive oil until well mixed, then immediately pour over tomatoes.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes, then serve.

title: layered pecan pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon of vanilla, beating until combined.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: real guacamole
directions: Smash 4 large avocados.
Add sour cream, onion (diced), garlic and lemon juice.
Add green or yellow chilies or diced green Ortegas.
Place pits in dish (keeps from turning color).
Use ingredient amounts to taste and sour cream to make smooth consistency.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and rice together; spread into greased baking dish. Lay chicken breasts on top of this mixture.
Sprinkle soup mixture on top of chicken.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover; bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mrs. bogle's cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately to first mixture with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham balls
directions: Form ingredients into balls.
Put on dish and chill.
Frost balls with 8 ounces cream cheese and enough sweet milk for a smooth texture.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Keep chilled.

title: the best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together the margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Then beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in the oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.

title: greek wedding cookies
directions: Allow sweet butter to soften to room temperature.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes, until white and creamy.
Add sugar, egg yolk, orange juice and brandy, beating all the while until thick as mayonnaise.
Sift flour and cornstarch into the bowl and continue mixing.
Finish by kneading for 5 minutes.
Add nuts last. Pinch off a small piece of dough.
(If dough is too soft to work with, do not add more flour, refrigerate for 1 or 2 hours.)
Shape dough in crescents or into small balls, but do not press down or make them flat.
This cookie does not rise during baking.
(Greek baker's shortcut:
Roll dough into a round log and cut diagonally into 1/2 inch thick slices.)
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1/2 inch apart.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
While cookies are baking, sift 1 cup confectioners sugar on a clean shallow pan or waxed paper spread on the counter.
Cover the bottom thickly.
Using a spatula, transfer hot cookies onto sugar gently, the moment you take them out of the oven.

Do not pile them on top of each other, but place them side by side as close as possible. Sift all the remaining sugar on top and sides through a strainer. Cool 4 hours before serving or transferring to a serving dish.
The cookies are better the next day and keep well.

title: chicken basting sauce
directions: Soak 4 to 8 chicken breasts for 1 to 4 hours, then broil.
Use remainder as basting sauce during broiling.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, cook stirring constantly until thick, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg yolks.
Cook 1 minute.
Add lemon peel, butter and lemon juice.
Stir until mixed.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and set overnight.
Serve with raw veggies or crackers.

title: bean dip
directions: Use fork to mix together the cream cheese and the refried beans.
On low to medium heat, melt cream cheese with beans.
Add hot sauce or salsa to your liking.
Serve warm.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O using directions on package.
After mixture is halfway set, add all other ingredients.
Pour in pan. Chill and serve.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in a small amount of fat and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer until tender.
Drain pineapple (reserve juice).
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Add to pork and simmer until thick.
Add pineapple, pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pralines
directions: Mix milk, sugar and pinch of soda.
Boil slowly and cook to soft boil stage, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until thick, then drop by tablespoonful on waxed paper.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients (including liquid) and beat for 4 minutes. Pour into oiled (lightly sprayed) 8 x 8 x 2 baking pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients,
add eggs and melted shortening. Bake on hot griddle until brown on each side.
Bake at 375°.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt and set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: st. peter's by the sea snapper
directions: Marinate the red snapper fillets in the lime juice for at least 1 hour at room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine the vinegar, parsley, green onion, white onion and garlic.
Slowly whisk in 1/2 cup of the oil, followed by the salt, pepper, hot pepper and tomato paste.
Whisk until the ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Set aside.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan with minced garlic and lemon juice.
Beat egg in bowl.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs in different bowl.
Pour a little melted butter mix into nonstick frypan.
Dip chicken in egg and then into bread crumbs.
Fry until tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water; beat.
Add pumpkin and mix.
Mix in dry ingredients; beat.
Fold in nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake at 325° in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: shannon's tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles as directed; drain.
Place cooked noodles in dish.
Add soup, Veg-All or peas, tuna and milk; stir together. Cover with bread crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake until bread crumbs are golden brown at 450° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 3 to 4 minutes, and enjoy!

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, salt, dill seed, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
(For first addition of flour, use mixer on low speed.)
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough; turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole.
Let rise in warm place until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: ultimate pumpkin roll
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium bowl.
Pour mixture into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. (When sides of cake pull away from pan, cake is done.)
Cool cake in the cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons 10x sugar on one side.
Flip cake over onto a sheet of waxed paper or towel.
Sprinkle other side of cake with 1 1/2 tablespoons 10x sugar.
Roll cake with the waxed paper into a jelly roll form. Cool completely while preparing cream cheese filling.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast and sugar to warm water. Stir until dissolved.

Add oil and salt. Stir. Add flour and knead about 5 minutes. Roll dough out as for biscuits. For regular rolls, stamp out with biscuit cutter and place barely touching in a greased baking pan (makes about 3 dozen).
For Parker House rolls, stamp out with biscuit cutter and place 2 portions in each cup of muffin tins. Brush tops with melted butter or oleo and let rise.
Bake in a 375° oven (top shelf) until golden brown.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and flour which have been sifted together.
Continue creaming until fluffy.
Add eggs, mixing until blended.
Add milk, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes longer, or when knife comes out clean.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place 1/2 teaspoon dill and mustard seed in each jar along with 2 slices of garlic and hot peppers. Wash and dry okra and pack in jars.
Do not bruise.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over okra in jars and seal, allow to stand two weeks before using.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour and slowly stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese.
Cook macaroni per directions.
Add cheese sauce.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix ham, horseradish and mustard and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine water and jello; mix with other ingredients and beat well. Bake in tube pan, well greased, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chili "on chips"
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine meat, tomato juice, kidney beans, stewed tomatoes and chili seasoning.
Bring to boil and stir; reduce heat and simmer until ready to eat.
Put corn chips in bottom of bowl; pour chili over chips.
Top with cheese; eat when cheese melts.
"Mmmm good."

title: pink lemondade pie
directions: Mix pink lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together.
Blend well by stirring.
Add Cool Whip and stir well until blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until set firmly.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix
ingredients
thoroughly.
Use 3 or 4 teaspoons per cup. Add hot water and a marshmallow.

title: cranberry glazed ham
directions: Cut fat several places around edge of ham slices.
Place one slice in greased baking dish. Cover with half of the mixture of cranberry sauce and corn syrup. Top with second slice of ham and cover with remaining cranberry mixture.
Stick whole cloves in fat around edges. Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Spray Pam in a 10 x 6-inch casserole.
Cover bottom with rice. Sprinkle with 1/2 of onion soup mix.
In separate pan, heat mushroom soup with chicken broth and pour 1/2 of mixture over rice. Place chicken pieces on top.
Pour remainder of soup mixture over the chicken and sprinkle the rest of the onion soup mix on top. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake for 1 hour more.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice enough peaches to cover a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut crust from bread and cut each slice into 5 fingers.
Place bread over fruit.
In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: crab spread
directions: In a dish, spread cream cheese.
Layer crab meat over cream cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce over top.
Arrange Pepperidge Farm fish shaped crackers around the dish to serve.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together for 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cereal and stir.
Press mixture in greased 12 x 17 x 1-inch pan.
Mix butterscotch and chocolate
chips together; spread over top.
Cut while still warm.

title: rhubarb-custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt; add to beaten eggs.
Stir in rhubarb.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Add onion, celery and pickle relish. Mix well. Fold in English peas. Chill before serving.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Wash and drain shrimp.
(Do not peel shrimp.)

Saute onions in cooking oil until soft and transparent. Add celery and green onions. Cook until tender. Stir in shrimp, salt, lemon juice and garlic powder. Cover and lower fire a little bit. When steam builds up in pot, stir or spin.
Cover. When liquid begins to build over shrimp, add liquid crab boil to taste. Stir again. Simmer about 15 minutes or until tender.
Turn heat off and let soak a few minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and seasonings.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Stir in milk.
(You can substitute 1 cup of corn liquid instead of milk.)
Stir in corn.
Pour into 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam and cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain off fat and set aside.
Mix together tomato sauce, cheese soup and seasonings. Mix together the sauce with the beef and macaroni.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1 cup grated Mozzarella cheese.
Top cheese with pepperoni and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Serve on lettuce with tostadas to dip.
If a warmer salad is desired, use same amount of jalapeno pepper instead of taco sauce.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine chestnuts, onions, celery, green pepper, corn, green beans, cheese and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole.
Combine margarine and crackers or corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Stir all together (except chicken and rice) and pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable baked fish
directions: Place 1/2 of vegetables in baking dish.
Season fish with herbs, salt and pepper and place on top of the vegetables.
Cover with remaining vegetables.
Add water.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: deviled tuna and noodles
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until soft. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
When slightly thickened, add tomato juice and combine with noodles, peas, tuna and olives.
Pour into buttered casserole and cover with crumbs.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes, until crumbs are brown.
Serves 8.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine apple juice and cereal (depending on the consistency you want, the cereal can be blended, crushed or left whole). Press the cereal-juice mixture into a 9-inch pie pan.
If you're using the crust for a pie which requires no baking, bake the crust for 10 minutes, then cool before filling.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Scald milk.
In a bowl mix 3 egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add to scalded milk and stir till it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Whip egg whites till stiff.
Pour over pie mixture and sprinkle with coconut.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes until brown.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients 2 minutes at medium speed. Put in half the batter (thawed and well drained).
Add rest of batter and sprinkle with another cup of.
Drizzle warm cake with 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: texas one dish dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles and drain.
Place half the noodles in buttered casserole.
Cover with meat mixture.
Add corn and tomato soup.
Add remaining noodles and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: simple raisin bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir in raisins.
Beat together buttermilk, brown sugar and melted butter at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, beat flour mixture into buttermilk mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, until well combined.
Spoon batter into prepared pan; smooth top.
Bake bread until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Transfer pan to wire rack to cool for 10 minutes. Loosen bread by running a metal spatula around sides of pan.
Turn bread out onto rack to cool completely.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix everything except butter and crackers in casserole dish. Top with crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheddar ham chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; do not drain.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat dry with paper toweling.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken pieces, broth, celery, onions and carrots in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Cover.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Cut meat from bones into bite size pieces; set aside. Reserve vegetables and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Remaining broth may be saved for next pot of soup.

title: cherry tomato dish
directions: Wash tomatoes and let dry or slice and drain. Butter an 8
x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place tomatoes evenly on bottom. Cover with onion and pepper.
Mix seasonings and bread crumbs and sprinkle
over
tomatoes.
Dot
with butter and cover with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in baking pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 1 hour.
Cook onion until soft in cooking oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over baked chicken; cook about 15 more minutes.
Serves 8.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is hot, pour mixture of lemon juice and powdered sugar over cake for glaze.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Mix and pat 1 1/2 cups flour, nuts,
sugar
and 3/4 cup butter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20
minutes
at
Set aside to cool.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, onion, pepper, celery and pimento.
Mix together sauerkraut juice, salad oil and sugar. Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sunshine noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix egg yolks and water; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Knead dough on lightly floured board until smooth.
Divide dough into 4 parts; roll each part separately until paper thin.
Let sheets of dough stand until partially dry.
Cut in narrow or broad strips.
Separate noodles and let dry another 30 minutes or longer.
Store in dry container in a cool, dry place.
Drop into boiling, salted water.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Put in hot serving dish.
Dress with melted butter or broth of your choice.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix together water and soda; set aside.
Blend together sugar and butter; add egg.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add water and soda; mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry
cake	and
pudding
mixes
with poppy seed; add water and oil.	Add
eggs,
one
at
a time, beating well after each	addition.
Pour
batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at	350° for 45 minutes. Allow cake to cool in pan for
minutes
before
removing.
Drizzle
with glaze made of confectioners sugar, lemon juice and butter.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put eggs, chicken, celery and sweet pickles through grinder. Add salt, pepper, mayonnaise and cream or milk.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper into a large bag.
Moisten potatoes and shake in bag until well coated.
Melt butter in baking dish; add potatoes and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Whip milk, eggs, sugar and melted butter until well blended. Add all other ingredients and beat with mixer or blender until lump free. Pour into uncooked pie crust. Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: like red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix well and drop on cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits. Bake until slightly brown.
Then brush top of hot biscuits with 1/4 cup melted butter and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: beef stew
directions: Toss flour and beef together in a 3-quart casserole until beef is coated.
Add remaining ingredients, except peas.
Microwave on 50% power for 50 to 60 minutes, until beef is fork-tender, stirring once.
Stir in peas.
Microwave 10 minutes more.
Let stand, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese in a large saucepan.
Add milk, mustard and pepper over low heat.
Stir often.
Add macaroni, veggies and Parmesan cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Add cranberry mixture to Jell-O and mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: potluck peas
directions: Fry bacon in skillet; remove, drain, crumble and set aside. In a small amount of the bacon grease, saute celery, onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add all tomatoes and cook together 15 to 20 minutes on low flame.
Add drained peas, salt and pepper. Cook 10 more minutes on low flame.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in 1 cup water.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish and put 1/2 cup crushed potato chips on top.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour in mixer.
Add softened butter and cream cheese, one tablespoon at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then vanilla.
Grease pan, put greased wax paper or parchment in bottom, and then flour.
Bake on lower middle of oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes for 1 large tube pan or about 50 minutes for 2 regular loaf pans.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and blend.
Mix in oleo, shortening and Steens (only) syrup.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed. Set aside.

title: catfish courtbouillon
directions: Season catfish with Cajun seasoning. Set aside. In Dutch oven, cook onions and bell peppers in melted butter until soft. Add garlic, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel.
