Simmer on low for 50 to 60 minutes. Stir occasionally. Stir in sugar. Add seasoned catfish. Simmer for 30 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with fork. Gently stir in green onions to not break fish apart. Simmer for 5 minutes. Serve over cooked white long grain rice.

title: ruth's rice pudding
directions: Combine milk and rice in deep heavy pan.
Simmer 45 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir frequently.
Mix in bowl canned milk, sugar, salt, eggs, cornstarch and vanilla.
Set aside until rice is done.
Combine above two parts and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Refrigerate.
Texture should be creamy and fluffy.
Milk can be added during serving if too thick. Sprinkle with cinnamon before serving.

title: eight can casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart casserole, mix everything except onion rings.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on onion rings and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust from graham crackers and melted butter.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased pie plate.
It will form its own crust.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: alecha
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender and golden.
Mix ginger, curry, salt, garlic and tomato paste to water.
Add to onion mixture.
Add 2 to 3 pounds of chicken to sauce; simmer until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Skinless chicken breasts work very well in this recipe.

title: apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie pan.
Beat egg with sugar until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts, apple and vanilla.
Bake in prepared pan 35 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: chicken-turkey casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Cook bell peppers, onions and garlic in melted margarine until just tender.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (be generous).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: easy hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, sugar and Cool Whip together. Cut Stella D'Oro puffs in half.
Fill with creamed mixture.
Put halves together and refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons of pineapple juice with pudding mix.
Mix together dairy whipped topping, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Add pudding and refrigerate.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix and vegetable oil.
Put crackers into a large bowl; pour mixture over crackers.
Mix well.
Place on baking sheet in a 350° oven; bake until crackers are golden brown. When cool, place in Ziploc storage bags.

title: seafood dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers, bread sticks or cut-up vegetables.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift again. Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and beat again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry beef and onion until browned.
Drain well and let cool. Blend cream cheese and salsa with hand mixer.
Chop lettuce.
Put lettuce on the bottom of a large pie pan.
Place beef then salsa mixture on lettuce and top with cheeses.
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fudge turnover cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease
bottom and sides of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine
in
casserole the flour, sugar, soda, salt,
vanilla
extract,
sour cream, shortening, chocolate, egg and 1/4 cup hot water.
Blend.
Beat vigorously with wooden spoon for
1 1/2 minutes.
Sprinkle pecans over batter. Cover with brown
sugar
and cocoa.
Pour 1 cup hot water over sugar mixture. Bake
at
350° for 50 to 55 minutes until cake springs back
when lightly touched.
Loosen edges with spatula (invert on plate immediately).

title: beer cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole or a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk on top of double boiler.
Stir mixture until melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, shortening and bananas; blend well.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Taste better if frozen, then thawed.
M-mmm good!

title: aunt beaut's ginger cakes(cookies)
directions: Mix molasses and soda.
Add sugar, lard, eggs and milk.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put in refrigerator a while. Roll on floured board about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cool and store in tightly closed container.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
While cake cools a little, mix pineapple and sugar; boil rapidly for 5 minutes.
Pour over warm cake; let cool.
Slice bananas and cover cake; spread prepared pudding over cake.
Mix pecans and coconut in Cool Whip.
Spread over pudding, then refrigerate.
Better if made 1 day before eating.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and bake in greased pan for 40 - 45 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour in greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: In oil, saute garlic; add spices and crushed tomatoes.
Simmer until sauce is reduced.
Add shrimp that have been peeled and deveined.
Cook for a few minutes until shrimp are tender.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw rice in casserole.
Brown chops in skillet and place on rice.
Place onion, tomato and pepper on each chop.
Pour beef bouillon over this.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add water, if desired.

title: hamburg goulash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper, onion and uncooked macaroni.
Mix tomato paste, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and add to meat mixture.
Cook about 20 minutes on top of stove in covered skillet.
If mixture seems to be drying out, add a little more liquid.
Cook only until macaroni is tender.

title: banana rum salsa
directions: *Dip basket tops in chocolate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook ground meat in skillet until done.
Drain; set aside. Boil noodles until desired fluffyness; drain.
Set aside. Combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, cream of onion soup (optional), sour cream and grated cheese in a large pot; heat to boiling.
Add drained ground meat and noodles; stir to keep from sticking.
Pour into large square baking pan.
Arrange bread pieces on top of mixture in baking pan; pour melted butter over top of bread. Bake until bread is toasted.
Let cool and serve. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: bren's raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water for 15 minutes.
Drain and reserve one cup liquid.
Let raisins cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and raisins.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add vanilla and reserved liquid.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Beat eggs,
salt,
flour and milk together.
In a skillet, melt butter, add apples and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour batter over apples and put in 400° oven.
Bake
to
25 minutes.
Turn onto plate and serve.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Cook garlic in hot oil.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil. Add pasta and mix well with cooked shrimp.

title: praline-yam casserole
directions: Cook yams in microwave or on stove until tender.
Peel and mash in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, 2 tablespoons oleo and salt.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart buttered casserole.
Arrange pecan halves over top.
Sprinkle with remaining brown sugar and drizzle the 1/4 cup melted oleo on top. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade salsa sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place milk in saucepan.
Heat until chocolate melts.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn in dish to form.

title: glaze for doughnuts
directions: Boil sugar, water and cinnamon for 5 minutes or just before it spins a thread.
Dip donuts and drain on wire rack.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugars, pecans and melted butter.
Mix until well blended.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels in unbaked pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Pie will become firm as it cools.

title: deviled crab
directions: Combine all ingredients lightly.
Shape into clean crab shells or spoon into casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bon bon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (medium). Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Measure flour. Blend in flour and salt. If dough is dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons cream. Wrap level tablespoon of dough around filling (a candied or well-drained maraschino cherry, pitted date, nut or chocolate piece). Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Cool. Dip tops of cookies in Icing. Decorate. Makes 20 to 25 cookies.

title: old-fashioned butter cookies
directions: In a 3-quart mixing bowl cream butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla until smooth and well combined.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm enough to roll.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out cookie dough, 1/2 at a time, on well floured surface 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake near center of oven for 6 to 10 minutes or until golden brown on edges.
Cool on wire rack.

title: caramel squares
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly in the pan with a spatula or by hand. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Melt caramels in the milk. Pour over crust and spread evenly.
Sprinkle chips over top of caramel.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; pour off excess oil.
Add vegetable soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in a mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to first mixture and beat well again.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix well. Bake in a tube pan which has been greased and dusted with flour. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix all together.
Layer cookie crumbs and pudding mixture in a sand bucket.
Start and end with cookie crumbs.
Place shovel in bucket.

title: crabmeat in shells(yields 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in Teflon skillet; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Add parsley, lemon juice, mustard and horseradish.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add eggs and crabmeat.
Place into shells and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Mix in applesauce; stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with white frosting.

title: tangy hollandaise sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double boiler and let stand for 30 minutes.
Bring water to a boil (water in bottom of double boiler should not touch top pan).
Reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until butter melts and sauce thickens, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot vegetables. Especially good on broccoli.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Test with a toothpick.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: texas best pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle or heavy skillet.
Use 1/4 measuring cup for regular size pancakes.
Use a tablespoon for dollar size pancakes. When bubbly and a little dry around the edge, turn over and brown other side.
Serve hot, with butter and syrup.
Cook any unused batter.
Freeze pancakes and just reheat.
They are like fresh ones.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Fry slowly in olive oil. Add to sauce and cook 2 hours.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound veal scallops and season with salt and pepper.
Flour and saute in olive oil until cooked.
Remove the scallops, set aside.
Degrease, then deglaze pan with marsala wine.
Add stock and sliced mushrooms; reduce until mixture begins to thicken. Return the scallops to sauce; add butter and cook until sauce becomes syrupy.
Plate veal and spoon sauce over veal.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Layer bread in bite size pieces in greased casserole.
Pour margarine over.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard and salt to eggs.
Add milk.
Mix. Pour over other ingredients in casserole.
Let stand minimum of 3 hours, preferably overnight in refrigerator covered. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350° covered.
May add onion flakes.
To double, use 3 pounds of shrimp.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Spread	broccoli
in
casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.	Combine
mayonnaise,
soup and lemon juice. Spread over
chicken
and	broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and spread bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben burger
directions: Combine meat, seed, garlic salt and lemon pepper; mix well. Shape into 6 patties.
In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Add sauerkraut and mix thoroughly; keep warm.
Broil patties.
Place each patty on slice of rye bread; top with sauerkraut, crumbled bacon, slice of cheese and slice of bread.

title: pineapple zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and sugar for 6 minutes.
Add pineapple and juice; cook 8 minutes.
Remove; add Jell-O.
Stir for 1 minute. Skim and put in jars.
Cool before covering.
Will be thin, but will thicken in refrigerator.
Freezes very well.
You can substitute any flavor of jello; orange works very well.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Pour out juice (liquid) from beans. Mix all ingredients in bowl. Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.

title: lightning coffee cake
directions: Mix the sugar, shortening, butter and flour well.
Set aside 1 cup of crumbs. Add the eggs, milk, baking powder and flour.
Beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and top with crumbs. Bake at 350°
until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pretty party punch
directions: Mix together and enjoy.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Grease a regular loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or use a nonstick pan and do not grease.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with water until just smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.

title: divinity surprise cookies
directions: Note:
These are drop cookies.
You will need cookie sheet lined with parchment.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add 2 cups of cooked pumpkin.
Add 4 cups milk and a little salt.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into prepared pie crusts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and bake until crust is firm.

title: oven roasted sauced spareribs
directions: Leave ribs whole or cut into serving pieces. Place in a large shallow pan. Roast at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine brown sugar, dry mustard and pepper in a saucepan; blend thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Pour 1/2 sauce over ribs and continue roasting for 30 minutes. Turn ribs and pour on remaining sauce. Roast 30 to 45 minutes longer or until meat is tender. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar and vanilla; mixing well.
Stir in butter and flour.
Chill 40 minutes.

title: smoked salmon log
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into log shape and roll in 1/2 cup nuts.

title: chess brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, mix cake mix and 1 egg.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1 stick butter.
Pack cake mix into bottom of pan after melting butter in it.
In a bowl, beat cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Add this mixture on top of cake mix. Bake approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fusilli with sauteed eggplant and feta cheese(quick and looks impressive!!!)
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water cook the fusilli until tender, but still firm.
While the fusilli is cooking, cut up the Feta cheese into 1/2 inch dice and put aside.
It's not necessary to be exact and don't worry if the Feta crumbles!
Cut the eggplant into 3/4 inch dice.
Heat the oil in a large, heavy frying pan.
Add the eggplant cubes and cook, stirring frequently, until the eggplant softens and begins to brown, about 5 minutes. Stir in the spaghetti sauce and Feta cheese and heat through. Drain the pasta.
Toss gently with the sauce and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heavenly hominy
directions: Place hominy in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Cut and dot hominy with margarine and 3/4 block of mild Mexican Velveeta. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cover dish with glass top or foil before baking; remove last 10 minutes if cheese isn't melting fast enough.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and rice summer salad
directions: Cook rice; combine with chicken and onion in bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.
Stir in almonds and grapes gently.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken. Debone and chop.
Lightly brown onion, pepper and garlic in margarine.
Add chili powder, tomato soup, mushroom soup and olives. Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Do not drain.
Add chicken and soup mixture to spaghetti.
Stir well.
Place in a large casserole dish. Cover with slices of Velveeta.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: dirty rice casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Melt margarine in skillet; add rice and onion and brown.
When browned, remove rice from heat.
Add pepper, bouillon and mushroom soup.
Pour into deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reuben
directions: Mix together in bowl with mayo to taste.
Serve on rye crackers or put on cocktail bread and heat until warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Mix well. Season to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, then top with crushed saltines.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until saltines are browned.

title: hashed brown omelet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute onion and green pepper; add potatoes. Add seasoning; cook over low heat about 20 minutes, or until underside is crisp and brown.
Blend eggs, milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; stir in cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover; cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Loosen edges; serve in wedges. Serves 4.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Arrange spaghetti in a shallow, greased baking pan.
Beat milk with eggs and pour over spaghetti.
Shake pan to settle spaghetti and distribute milk.
Spread top evenly with spaghetti sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into wedges or squares.

title: my favorite easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and paprika until well blended.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and/or paprika during the last 10 minutes of baking time.
Serves 8.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Divide the lettuce among 4 plates, cover and set aside. In a large bowl, combine the chili powder and cumin. Add the chicken, turning to coat. Lift chicken from bowl, shaking off the excess coating. Heat the oil in a wide nonstick frying pan or wok over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the chicken and stir fry gently until no longer pink in the center. Cut to test. Pour salsa over chicken and cook, stirring until the salsa is heated through and thickened. Arrange chicken and salsa over the lettuce. Top with sour cream and cilantro sprigs if using. This has 12 grams carbohydrate.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown chops on all sides in hot fat. Place apple slices in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; dot with butter.
Top with chops.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas wreath cookies(yields 2 dozen)
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Add remaining ingredients, adding corn flakes last, and mix.
Form into wreaths on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with red candies (silver shot or candied cherries) to resemble bows or holly berries.
Let set until firm. Very pretty on a cookie tray with assorted cookies.

title: oven baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Mix.
(May make ahead and refrigerate at this point, but leave out croutons and mix in just before baking.)
Spread into casserole, then add cheese and chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly. Increase baking time if refrigerated.
Serves 12.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat eggs light.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased and floured pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350°.

title: quick thick clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, mix potato slices, sauce mix, amounts of water and milk called for on package, clam liquor, green onion and green pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams, 2 1/2 cups milk and the butter; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Cook until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup butterscotch chips together over hot water.
Stir well.
Spread evenly over Rice Krispies.
Cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Very good with any dried beans.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add taco sauce, chilies, salt and pepper.
Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with meat sauce.
Add chopped cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over chips.
Garnish with olives, sour cream and/or avocado dip as desired.

title: popcorn crumble
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and cook to 300° using a candy thermometer. Add vanilla and very quickly pour over popcorn mixture.
Stir to coat well and spread on a greased cookie sheet to harden.
Makes 1 pound.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all ingredients and mix just before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook down until thick.
Put in sterilized jars and process in water bath for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pick meat off bones.
Cook egg noodles, then drain.
Add soups.
Next, add peas and meat.
Stir it all up.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mash beans with liquid.
Add cooked beef, catsup, onion, chili powder and hot sauce.
Heat on top of stove in a Pyrex dish. Layer green onions around outer edge, then a ring of olives with cheese in center.
Place in a hot oven or microwave just long enough to melt cheese.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Yields 3 to 4 cups.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Ladle pancake batter onto medium to hot griddle in 1/4 cup measurements.
Turn when bubbles form on pancake.
Serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet until brown.
Add chili beans, hominy, cream of chicken soup and chili powder.
Put in a casserole dish.
Put in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Return to oven until the cheese melts.

title: holiday potato dish(scalloped)
directions: Remove skins from potatoes; shred into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup melted butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in soup, cheese and sour cream.
Add potatoes and toss until coated with soup/cream mixture.
Drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter and bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in 350° oven for one hour.
Garnish with pimento and parsley.

title: joyce's maple syrup
directions: Place sugars in saucepan.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over sugars and stir gently.
After sugars are dissolved and come to a boil, add maple and vanilla extracts.
Stir.
Mix until extracts are blended in.
Place in container.

title: green noodle chicken casserole
directions: Cook
noodles.	Mix chopped chicken and all ingredients except grated cheese.
Combine noodles and chicken mixture and put in one
10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake for
minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: au gratin potatoes (fancy)
directions: Cook
potatoes.
Peel
and shred.
When cooled melt 3/4 of a stick
of
margarine in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add potatoes, soups, sour cream and onions.
Melt remaining 1/4 stick of margarine
and pour over corn flake crumbs.
Add corn flake crumb mix
to
cheese
and then top potato mixture with cheese mix. Bake 55 minutes with 12 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in a little oil.
Add lots of ketchup until boiling.
Add a little vinegar (2 tablespoons or so).
Add about 1/2 to 3/4 cup of honey.
Cook all this on top of stove for 45 minutes to 1 hour, then brush on meat.

title: convection oven oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven broiling rack in lower guides.
Preheat oven to 325°. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into large bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from sheet.

title: super soup croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toast bread slices on light setting to dry them out.
If the bread is stale, you may eliminate this step! Melt the butter or margarine.
Trim the crusts from the bread.

title: tater dipped veggies
directions: In a small bowl, combine potato flakes, cheese, celery salt, garlic powder and butter.
In another bowl, beat the eggs.
Dip vegetables, one at a time, in eggs, then potato mixture.
Coat well.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with your choice of dressing or dip.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 of sugar.
Add pumpkin, milk, salt, mace and cinnamon.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly about 10 minutes, remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Let this cool. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture and put in baked pie shell.
Top with cream.

title: quick yellow cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and beat for two minutes at medium speed.
Scrape sides of bowl while beating.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until it passes the toothpick test.
(Florence suggests the following boiled frosting recipe for a cake topping.)

title: stuffed, baked zucchini squash
directions: Parboil squash; cool, cut lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese.
Stuff into split squash. Top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until meat is brown and cheese melted.
Can freeze and bake later.

title: creamy garden salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add carrots, bacon, onion and cheese.
In small bowl, mix Miracle Whip, sugar, vinegar and bacon drippings.
Pour over vegetables and stir to coat.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: Chop and brown onion and pepper in shortening in frypan.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and cook in a 2-quart casserole dish, covered.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in uncooked pie shell.
Beat other ingredients into custard.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour until custard is set.
Make meringue with egg whites.
Place on top of custard.
Bake until golden brown.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Warm cottage cheese; add remaining ingredients, mix and cover.
Let stand until double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Punch down.
Place in well greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole or 2 small loaf pans.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pasticcio
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Spread half of the macaroni in greased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Cover with beef mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup of the cheese and the cinnamon; sprinkle over beef mixture.
Cover beef mixture with remaining macaroni.

title: fruit cake(from 1879 cookbook)
directions: Let rise about 3 hours, then bake slowly.
Let stand a good while after it is baked.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt; add corn and milk.
Bake in 2 or 2 1/2-quart baking dish at 350° for about 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pudding.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar, Wesson oil and butter; add well beaten eggs and beat.
Crush bananas and add.
Sift flour and measure; add spices and soda.
Add to other mixtures and beat well.
Save 1/2 cup flour to roll raisins in.
Add nuts and vanilla last.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil Eagle Brand milk in can for 3 hours (add water as it evaporates).
Let cool.
Layer bananas, pineapple and Eagle Brand milk in crust twice.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon-cheese jello salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and pineapple.
Cook until all sugar is dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and chill until it reaches syrup stage.
Fold in nuts, grated cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Chop cherries and pineapple fine.
Chop pecans.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add flour and baking powder mixture to butter mixture.
Add flavorings.
Pour over chopped fruit and pecans. Stir well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Be sure to get fruit and pecans covered well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.
May be longer depending on your oven.

title: orange congeal salad
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water. Add to cream cheese and beat until cheese has melted. Take meat from oranges and add with chopped nuts and drained pineapple to cream cheese mixture. Chill.

title: summer dressing
directions: Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and stir.

title: sopaipillas(fried bread with honey)
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder; cut shortening into mixture with two knives until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Stir in warm water until moist.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes. Cover dough with plastic wrap or towel for 30 minutes.
Cut dough in half on lightly floured surface, roll dough out, make into balls and then roll each flat like a tortilla.
Fry over medium-high heat until puffy and golden brown.
Note:
If they do not puff, oil is not hot enough.
Serve immediately with honey, sugar or preserves. Makes 35 to 40.

title: summertime pasta salad
directions: Combine vinegar and next 4 ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Combine macaroni with ham and next 3 ingredients.
Add dressing and mix.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings (about 9 cups).

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Brown heaping spoonful of cornmeal in oil in skillet.
Add salt gradually.
Add milk and cook until thick.

title: wieners in sauce
directions: Mix and heat thoroughly until wieners swell.

title: doggie biscuits(your dogs love cookies, too!)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl, mix flours, bulgur, cornmeal, dry milk and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add yeast mixture and 2 cups broth to dry ingredients; mix well with hands.
Dough will be very stiff, so add more broth if necessary.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; brush lightly with egg-milk mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes; turn oven off and let biscuits remain in closed oven overnight to harden.
Makes 11 dozen 3-inch biscuits.

title: susan's carrot chowder
directions: Brown hamburger or ground chuck or ground turkey; drain. Cover and simmer meat, salt, celery, green onion, onion and potato on low until tender.
In a large saucepan, put tomato juice, celery soup, water, carrots, garlic, marjoram, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, then add hamburger.
Simmer together 30 minutes. Pour into bowls over grated cheese.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: Saute shrimp and clams in olive oil until cooked to your liking.
Add clam sauces and garlic.
Simmer for 1/2 hour over low heat; cook linguini until tender.
Add butter.
Pour cooked ingredients over linguini and serve hot.

title: mountain stew
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add salt to taste.
Dice up small onion.
Cook with meat until tender.
Add kidney beans and pork and beans.
Add 1/2 cup catsup.
(Add 1 to 2 tablespoons mustard for a completely different taste.) Stir up well.
Serve with crackers.

title: salsa
directions: Cut lemon in slices.
Cut hot chili into small size.
Place everything into the food processor and mix.
Add some flavoring powder, if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce with meatballs
directions: Beat egg in milk and add all spices.
Break up bread and let soak for awhile.
Add meat and onion.
Mix and make into meatballs.
Brown.

title: jello squares
directions: Mix 1 large or 2 small packages (same flavor) of Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.

Put in 13 x 9-inch pan; let set for 2 hours. Mix 1 1/2 envelopes Knox gelatine with 1/2 cup boiling water. Bring 1 cup heavy cream and 1/2 cup sugar to a boil, then add to plain gelatine with 1 cup sour cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
Spoon over congealed Jell-O.
Let stand for 2 hours.

title: taste of autumn pancake syrup(10 out of 10 kids love this one!)
directions: Mix cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water until smooth.
In a saucepan, combine the cornstarch liquid, remaining water and juice concentrate.
Cook over medium heat until the syrup thickens. Stir constantly.
When thickened, add maple extract and nutmeg. Serve warm.

title: monster cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients together until well blended.
Cream together next 5 ingredients thoroughly in extra large bowl.
Gradually mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture until mixed well.
Roll into cookie balls and flatten with hands. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: creamy marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme, Hershey bar and chocolate chips in large bowl.
Set aside.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Remove peel from 3 large oranges or grapefruit.
Cut peel into long strips, 1/4 inch wide.
Place in 2 quart saucepan; cover with water and bring to boil over full heat; drain.
Cover with more cold water and repeat the cooking and draining process 3 more times.
Cover again with water and cook peel for 15 minutes after water reaches boiling point.
Drain thoroughly.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups water and cook over low heat until syrup almost evaporates, about 45 minutes.
Watch continuously so that peel doesn't stick and scorch.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on breadboard. (I usually have to add more)
Lift peel out and place on sugared board.
Mix until all sides are thickly coated with sugar.
Dry on cake rack.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups peel.

title: pecan-streusel coffee cake
directions: For topping:
In a mixing bowl, stir together pecans, brown sugar, margarine or butter and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Combine dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Leave in pan 5 to 15 minutes after taking from oven.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: veal scallopini with lemon and capers
directions: Combine flour and pepper on a plate.
Press veal pieces into the mixture, coating them all over and shaking off any excess.

title: candied nuts
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and allspice in a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Bring to boiling; boil over medium heat until reduced to 1/3 cup.
Add nuts all at once; stir quickly to coat all nuts.
Spread candy on a baking sheet or aluminum foil, breaking up large clumps of nuts with a spoon.
After candy cools, break apart into individual nuts.
Store in an airtight tin at room temperature for up to 1 month.

title: choc-choc cake
directions: Mix together 4 minutes; fold in chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350° in tube pan.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and salt. Add soda and vanilla.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Add flour and cinnamon last!
Bake in tube pan 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: pepparkakor #8
directions: Cream first four ingredients well. Sift dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture. Blend well. Chill dough (overnight is best). Roll out very thin and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° 10-12 minutes. The dough may be frozen and keeps for a long time.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour in pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add jello, blueberries and cool.
Add bananas. This makes 3 pies, use 3 graham cracker pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: paul horining stew
directions: Cube meat and cut vegetables to bite size pieces.
Use the juice from the peas for liquid.
Cut bread into small pieces.
Mix all together in a large pan and add tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours or longer.

title: red snapper citrus
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine onion, orange juice and orange rind and salt.
Marinate fillets in mixture for about 30 minutes. Drain and bake, flesh side up, for about 12 minutes or until done. Just before baking, sprinkle each fillet lightly with nutmeg and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook and debone chicken; set aside.
Mix flour, shortening, salt and pepper.
Then add liquid from chicken.
Mix well.
Form into balls.
Roll very thin on a well-floured board.
Cut into strips and then cut into squares and drop into boiling broth.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.

title: vegetable 'n cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in celery, carrot and onion.
Over medium heat, cook for 10 minutes; stir occasionally (do not brown).
Add water, bouillon and pepper sauce; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in mashed potato flakes slowly.
Add milk and cheese, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Do not boil. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: play dough
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, mix water, salt, cream of tartar and vegetable oil.
Add food coloring.
Stir well and add flour. Mix well and cook until thick.
Cool before use.
May need kneading to fully mix in flour.

title: simple macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients with the cooked macaroni.
Mix well.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and carrots in casserole. Sprinkle each layer with a little salt and flour.
Lay pork chops on top; season chops to taste.
Pour water, then milk, over chops. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 1 hour, or until chops are brown and potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: peanut butter-chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream peanut butter and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chunks.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, spacing 3 inches apart. Bake for 14 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add pudding mixes, milk and almond extract.
Add Cool Whip to top.
Sprinkle with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate until served.

title: pizza pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
You may add other ingredients according to preference.
After you refrigerate, you may need to add more dressing to coat.
Makes plenty.

title: 10 minute tomato soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, heat the tomatoes until boiling. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Return to heat and cook on medium until butter is melted and the soup is heated through.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat, cook; add confectioners sugar, beating well after each addition.
Fills and frosts top and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer cake.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary. Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan or broiler-proof dish, skin side up.
Broil until browned.
Stir sauce; pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange lemon and pineapple slices around chicken.
Spoon sauce from baking pan over all; continue baking for 5 minutes.
Garnish with fresh rosemary or parsley. Makes 6 servings.
Preparation:
10 minutes.
Baking:
40 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers in round slices.
Put in gallon glass jar.
Add salt.
Cover with water.
Let sit 1 week.
Remove and wash in cold water, about 3 times.
Cover with water.
Add powdered alum.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain. Mix in other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In blender, blend bananas, adding eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Blend well.
Sift flour in a large bowl.
Mix all and add nuts.
Stir again.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: western hash
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper, onion, tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese slices and heat until melted.

title: escalloped corn supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces, cut each breast half into halves and remove skin.
Heat butter and oil in 13 x 9-inch pan in 375° oven until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken. Place chicken meat side down in pan, turning to coat with herb mixture.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, cook until thickest pieces are done (about 30 minutes, longer).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together until smooth. Roll into one inch balls. Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork into criss-cross pattern. Bake at 300 degrees until brown, about 8-10 minutes.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix the cornmeal with salt, egg and buttermilk. Add hot melted bacon fat.
Pour into greased iron skillet and bake at 375° until done.

title: hanky-pankies
directions: *Sausage according to your taste, mild, hot or half and half.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch round pan.
Combine all ingredients and stir just until blended.
Spread in prepared pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Blend with sugar.
Add melted oleo, then milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pastry.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Add egg and vanilla; add flour mixture and form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with a chocolate candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Makes 3 dozen.
Very good!

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten each breast half to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place one slice of ham and 1 slice cheese in center of each breast. Sprinkle parsley and pepper on each one.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with toothpicks.

title: mushrooms with paprika
directions: Brown the finely chopped onion in the fat.
Then add the parsley and the cleaned, washed and chopped mushrooms.
Cook until moisture evaporates.
Add salt and paprika.
Stir for a moment and pour in the cream and boil once.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well.
Add oil, vanilla, water and vinegar.
Mix with a spoon just until all ingredients are mixed.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Very moist and keeps well.

title: favorite jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add yogurt, pineapple and nuts.
(Only add bananas if salad will be eaten in 1 day, as they will turn dark.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except Jiffy mix.
Mix in Jiffy mix last. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until golden brown at 400°.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Add the flour.
Add milk and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll out and pat thin. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375°.

title: carrot and onion bake
directions: Place carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and saute onion until tender. Add sugar and salt. Add parsley and mix well.
Spread onion mixture over carrots.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Add cream and bake 5 to 8 more minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon and cocoa.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, zucchini, oil, pecans and vanilla.
Pour flour into batter and mix thoroughly
Spray two
9 x 5-inch loaf pans with vegetable spray. Divide batter equally between the 2 pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until firm.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Allow to cool thoroughly before slicing.
Yields 2 loaves.
One-twelth loaf contains 246 calories (47% from fat).

title: family favorite pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bulgoki(korean food)
directions: Pour sake in the sliced beef.
Add sugar, soy bean sauce and black pepper in beef mixture.
Slice onion.
Chop the green onion. Chop the garlic.
Slice carrots.
Steam broccoli.
Mix all together.
Add sesame oil.
Heat the pan.
Add corn oil lightly and cook over medium heat.

title: chicken continental
directions: In skillet, brown chicken and mushrooms in butter.
Stir in soup, water, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes. Stir in rice.
Simmer 10 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla milk
directions: Heat milk in microwave or on stove.
Remove from heat before boiling.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Enjoy!

title: microwave squash casserole
directions: Microwave squash and onions covered in 2 quart dish on high for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on medium for 8 minutes.
Let stand for 3 minutes.

title: creamy turkey bake
directions: Cook rice in chicken stock or consomme.
Do not drain rice. Add mayonnaise, turkey or chicken, eggs, cheese, onion, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in large, buttered casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, peanut butter and margarine with hands into a big ball.
Chill 2 hours.
Break apart and roll with hands into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate until well coated.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream
the
margarine
or butter and the softened cream cheese until
fluffy.
Add
sugar
and
continue beating. Add vanilla. Add
cake
flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending
with the
flour.
Continue
beating until well mixed. Pour into	well greased
and
floured tube pan and place in a cold oven.
Bake
for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Cool in pan for approximately 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch apple dumplings
directions: Roll dough thin (flour, salt, baking powder and shortening). Cut into squares.
Place apple halves on dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bring dough together over apples.
Place in greased pan.
Heat boiling water, butter and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: freeze ahead appetizers
directions: Mix and spread on muffin halves.
Cut each half into 8 small wedges.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Put into Baggies.
When needed, pop into oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: summer vegetable bake
directions: Slice vegetables thin.
Slice onion very thin.
Layer vegetables in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with dried bread crumbs and Italian seasoning.
Put a layer of cheeses over this and repeat sequence.
Cheddar, Muenster, Mozzarella, Provolone and Parmesan all work well in this recipe; choose any combination that suits your taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Press in pie shell.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: red cabbage
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the salt, in a 10 to 12-quart stainless steel pot.
Bring to a boil; stir, cover and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste.

title: broccoli noodle cheese soup
directions: Heat butter; add onion and saute.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Add noodles and salt and boil 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic; cook for 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper; cook until cheese is melted.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Put pineapple, sugar and Jell-O in pan.
Bring to a boil. Cool to room temperature.
Then fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour in a 6-cup mold.

title: pumpkin bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with a nonfat cooking spray.
In a medium bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
In a large bowl using a wire whisk, beat egg substitute.
Stir in pumpkin, cereal, milk and corn syrup. Add to flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Take an inexpensive cut of beef roast, chuck roast or bottom round roast and place on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Surround it with carrots, small potatoes and small onions.
(I poke holes through the center of onions so they hold their shape.)
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over the beef.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of dry Lipton onion soup mix on top.
You may also put in some mushrooms. Wrap completely, securely in the foil.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 3 hours (it will make its own gravy).

title: pat's fruit tart
directions: Slice cookie dough.
Line in ungreased 14-inch pizza pan or 2 small quiche pans, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 275° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; cool.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add oil and chocolate; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in zucchini and 1 cup nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: prune-stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Bring prunes and broth to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and let stand 20 minutes.
Saute celery and onion in oil until tender.
Place bread cubes and poultry seasoning in a large bowl; toss to mix.
Add celery, onion, prunes and broth.
Toss lightly to blend.
Add more broth if dressing too dry.
Trim excess fat from tenderloin.
Cut lengthwise to within 1/2-inch of each end and almost to the bottom, leaving bottom connected.
Open out the meat and pound the side of the pocket to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine garlic, fennel seeds, pepper and salt and rub on the inside of the pocket.
Spoon stuffing into opening of tenderloin.
Press gently to close.
Tie tenderloin securely with heavy string at 1-inch intervals.
Place tenderloin on roasting rack.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of tenderloin. Place rack in roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of tenderloin.
Place tenderloin in oven preheated to 500°. Immediately reduce temperature to 350°.
Cook 20 minutes, then brush on melted butter and cook additional 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cover with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Slice into 4 equal servings.

title: fresh pea salad
directions: Mix well and serve cold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in next 5 ingredients with a large spoon.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edges.)
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: gloria june's chicken
directions: Mix cut up chicken, soups, milk and onion in casserole dish. Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour chicken stock over stuffing. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: linguine with shrimp(linguine con gamberi)
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Wash thoroughly under cold water and blot dry with paper towel.
Set aside.

title: chunky italian soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink, drain.
Return mixture to pan.
Stir in tomatoes and next 7 ingredients, and, if desired, chili powder bring to a boil, then simmer stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans and next 3 ingredients; simmer, stir occasionally, 15 minutes.
Stir in pasta. Sprinkle each serving with cheese. Yield 10 cups.

title: sloppy joe sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion in a skillet and drain off excess fat.
Combine beef and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes and serve on buns.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Reduce heat to medium. Stir in flour until completely blended.
Add water, bouillon, garlic and pepper.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and add broccoli and milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in half and half.
Add cheese.

title: simply zucchini(microwave)
directions: Prepare zucchini.
Scrub and rinse well.
Cut lengthwise into 6 sections.
Cut each section in half.
Place in microwave-safe dish.
Add juice, water, butter and pepper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until tender; do not overcook.

title: tex-italia pie
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
Cook, using package directions; drain.
Place in large bowl.
Add eggs and 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Spread onto 12-inch pizza pan.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Make
batter
from the first seven ingredients and pour into greased baking pan, 8 x 10 x 2-inch.
Add canned fruit or berries and water.	(If the fruit or berries are juicy, do not add the water.) Bake one hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Add soda to dates.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Beat eggs; add 1 cup sugar and melted shortening.
Combine this mixture with hot dates.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold chopped nuts into mixture.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Put layer in bowl, then top with Cool Whip, then more squares, etc.

title: frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk.
Cook on low heat until its thick and smooth.
Set aside and let cool.
Then mix remaining ingredients until smooth, about 15 minutes.
Add milk slowly and mix together until fluffy like cream.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar, milk, butter and salt. Bring to a full boil and cook at boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and all chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir quickly as this thickens quickly.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: meringue squares
directions: Cream margarine with 1/3 cup sugar; add egg yolks; beat well. Add sifted flour.
Put mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Press and shape in pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Meanwhile, make a meringue of the two egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar. Fold in chopped nuts.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Let batter set for 30 minutes.
Stir in onion rings, deep fry until they turn brown.

title: woolly bear dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, fold in sour cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, yellow cake mix, coconut and nut meats.
Next melt margarine.
Place melted margarine over the nut meats. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add everything but water.
Beat 2 minutes and then stir in water.
Pour in two 9-inch or three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch cake pan and sprinkle almonds in bottom of pan.
Melt butter in a saucepan and add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil, stirring constantly, for 6 1/2 to 7 minutes. Immediately pour over almonds in buttered pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot toffee and cover with a plate or lid to melt chips. Once the chips are melted, spread evenly over toffee and refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Break and store in cool place.

title: busy day pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Put flour, sugar and milk in a bowl and mix until smooth.
Pour mixture over margarine.
Drain peaches and place evenly in mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato biscuit
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in Crisco; add sweet potatoes.
Stir until mixed, all ingredients moist. Sprinkle milk over dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Roll; cut. Bake in 450° oven 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients in bean pot or 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with an electric mixer until blended. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until set or freeze.

title: viennese raspberry squares
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, bring egg whites to room temperature. Set aside.
For crust, in another medium mixing bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium-high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add about half the flour.
Then add the sugar and egg yolks.
Beat on medium-high speed until thoroughly combined.
Stir in remaining flour.
Press crust mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bailey's
directions: Blend 1 minute in blender.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add well beaten eggs, flour, cinnamon, milk and flavoring.
Add remaining ingredients, all chopped.
Drop on well-greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: bagels
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients and let rise until double in size.
Punch down and form rings.
Let rise until double.
Drop in 6 quarts boiling water.
Boil for 3 minutes. Place on baking sheet; bake for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread bread cubes and add sausage. Sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs and other ingredients.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: super beans
directions: Brown the hamburger and chopped onions, drain well.
Combine all other ingredients.
(Drain lima and red beans.)
Bake at 350° for one hour in large casserole or roaster.
Cover during the first half of baking time and uncover for the last half of time.

title: chocolate peanut-butter-cup cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cocoa powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla about 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat until thoroughly blended.
Reduce speed to low, gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir peanut butter cup pieces and chocolate chips into dough.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheets, using 3 tablespoons per cookie, spacing 1 inch apart.
bake 13 to 15 minutes until dry and slightly firm. Cool1 minute on cookie sheets.
Cool completely on wire racks. Makes 2 dozen.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl and chill.
Serves 6.

title: sparkle party
directions: Sit in a circle in a dark room.
One at a time, chew on a Life Saver with your mouth open.
Watch the sparkles!

title: mushroom beef skillet
directions: Broil steak 6 inches from the heat until rare, about 5 minutes on each side.
Cut diagonally into thin strips; set aside and keep warm.
In a large skillet, bring broth to a boil.
Add onion and mushrooms; cover and simmer until tender, about 5
minutes.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Toss lightly.
Roll pie crust and place in tin.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon flour in bottom of pan.
Spoon apple mixture into crust.
Slice butter and put it on top of apples. Top with second crust; flute edges and cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender and top is golden brown.
Cover the edge of crust with strips of foil for 15 to 20 minutes of baking time to prevent excessive browning. Serves 8.

title: peanut soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Process onion, ground peanuts and potatoes in processor.
Add broth gradually.
Heat to serve, adding cream or milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with chives.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: *Do not use margarine.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Once mixed, split in half for 2 loaves, if desired. In a large pan or 2 small pans, shape into loaves.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
A large loaf serves 8, small serves 4.

title: yummies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Top with topping.

title: carrot sandwiches
directions: This works better if carrots are grated finely and then measured.
The same for the nuts.
I use only enough mayonnaise to make spreadable.
Also garlic powder to taste.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, beaten eggs and butter; fold in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add water to reserved pineapple juice to measure 2 cups.
Heat to boiling and pour over Jell-O to dissolve.
Chill Jell-O until it begins to set.
Add cream cheese (which has been softened with cream).
Mix with rotary beater.
Add celery, nuts and pineapple. Pour into molds and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg and next 4 ingredients.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meatballs, then pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in separate saucepot, stirring constantly until jelly is melted.
Add to meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: brandied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 45 minutes or until tender. Cool to touch. Peel and mash potatoes. Stir in sugar and next 6 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Brush top with tablespoon of melted butter. Sprinkle with orange rind. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Garnish with orange slices, if desired. Yields 8 servings.

title: antipasto for eight
directions: Use large round platter or Lazy Susan.
Arrange tuna fish in center and surround with all other ingredients, forming a pattern. Serve with a cruet of olive oil and vinegar for individual seasoning.

title: indian shuck bread
directions: Shuck and clean ears of roasting corn.
Boil on the cob about 10 minutes.
Whole ears of corn may then be packed into a clean crock, or cut from the ear.
Add a solution of salted water or sprinkle salt over corn in layers, then add water.
When corn is pickled, it may be eaten from the cob or cut off and fried in butter or other fat.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar together. Heat margarine, cocoa and cola until mixture comes to a boil. Pour the mixture over flour and sugar. Blend and add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Fold in marshmallows. Beat well by hand and pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture seems firm.

title: squash fritters
directions: Variation:
One-fourth cup grated bell peppers or garlic.

title: lallie's chocolate pie(my mother's recipe of 50 years)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in boiler.
Add milk slowly.
Bring to a boil.
Beat yolks in slowly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put in baked pie shell.
Cover with egg whites (as meringue).
Brown.

title: italian sausage in tomato sauce
directions: Saute Italian sausage for a few minutes in olive oil, just long enough to seal it or firm it up.
Remove sausage and let cool.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in the skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Add sausage and cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Serve as a hot appetizer.
You may wish to be cautious with the wine at first.
Some may find 1 cup too much.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil noodles and drain.
Add noodles to the tuna fish, mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Add milk and spices.
Cook for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and make into small balls.
Brown slightly in frying pan.
Drain.
Mix together chili sauce and grape jam.
Simmer slowly for about an hour.
I use crock-pot to simmer.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; combine onion, mayonnaise, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Layer macaroni and soup mixture. Sprinkle cheese and pimento.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy lemon cake
directions: Cream together margarine, lemon extract and vanilla extract. Blend in 1 1/4 cup sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Fill and frost with a lemon 7-Minute Frosting.

title: chocolate-covered fruit
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan.
Stir in heavy cream. Keep chocolate warm in fondue pot and dip in the fruit or dip the fruit halfway in and place on a waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla, margarine, sugar and egg.
Add flour, salt, soda and yogurt.
Add poppy seed.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with some sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Cool.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all together and pour into popsicle molds; freeze.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Place paper cupcake liners in 30 muffin cups. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full of batter.

title: hot buttered rum batter
directions: Whip all ingredients together and chill.
To Serve:
Use 1 Tbsp. per cup.

title: chit'lins
directions: Thoroughly wash chit'lins; need to get rid of all the excess fat, grease and dirt.
Change water often, until it rinses clear. Place clean chit'lins in a large pot, together with the onion, garlic, bay leaf, salt, pepper, vinegar and Tabasco sauce. Do not add water.
Bring slowly to a boil over medium heat; quickly reduce heat and simmer slowly for about 2 hours.
Remove excess water as it builds up.
The chit'lins will remain watery, but do not allow them to become saturated.
After 2 hours, cut the chit'lins into pieces.
Continue simmering them and removing the excess liquid for another 1 1/2 hours or until they become fork-tender.
When done, season to taste with additional salt, pepper, vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Serve with greens and potato salad or slaw and cornbread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a bowl, combine the peanut butter, vanilla, oleo and nuts. Mix sugar, milk and Karo in saucepan; bring
to a boil.
Pour in browned sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Pour into peanut butter mixture and beat until it holds shape.
Spread into buttered dish.

title: spaghetti-chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and put in casserole dish.
Saute onion in oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and red pepper and heat to boiling.
Add chicken and mushrooms, then pour over spaghetti.
Toss with a fork.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until mixture is heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop green pepper, tomato and onion.
Add to pasta and mix. Add salad dressing until pasta is coated.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme spice until desired taste.
Toss well.
Serve well chilled.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add cut up hot dogs.

title: microwave baked ziti
directions: Combine ziti and spaghetti sauce in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered with lid, at High 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir twice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.

title: microwave zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in microwave for 8 minutes.
Add carrots and onion.
Cook for 4 more minutes.
Stir in stuffing, saving some to sprinkle on top.
Also, stir in the sour cream.
Cook 4 more minutes or until hot.

title: chow mein
directions: Heat oil in skillet; fry meat alone until nearly done.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce, celery, onions and 1 1/2 cups soup stock or bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 cups water.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, drained.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add gravy, using 1 tablespoon bead molasses, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, cornstarch and 2/3 cup water.
Season to taste.
Pour over meat and vegetables; stir until thickened.
Serve over canned noodles or rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in 9 X 13 baking pan. Lay chicken breast on rice. Sprinkle soup mix on chicken. Top with chicken soup and broth. Cover with foil and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Add the soups, water and cooked macaroni.
Mix well and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Combine shrimp, celery and onion in a saucepan with enough water to cover (1 cup).
Simmer over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Add potatoes, milk and margarine.
Heat; season to taste and serve.

title: blueberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Combine pumpkin and milk until blended.
Cream shortening and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add egg; beat until mixture is fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beating well after each addition.
Combine blueberries and flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Fill 18 paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel over top of muffins.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with sliced fruit.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Shape into 2 logs or balls.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with additional olives.

title: fourth of july dessert
directions: Take angel food cake and cut up in bite size pieces; take strawberries, blueberries, walnuts and bananas and mix up in large bowl. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill. Great summer dessert!

title: spinach with hearts of palm
directions: In a glass baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray, place chopped hearts of palm along the bottom.
Squeeze all liquid from spinach.
In skillet, melt 1 Tbsp. margarine.
Add spinach; heat and add flour, yogurt, milk, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread over hearts of palm.
In remaining margarine, saute mushrooms.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mushrooms over spinach mixture (may be prepared day before to this point).
Cover with topping.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: catfish stew
directions: Clean and wash catfish. Cut up catfish to desired size pieces. Put 2 cups water in pot and add onions. Bring to a boil. Add catfish, bacon drippings and seasonings to water and onions.
Let cook for 10
minutes.
Make a thickener of flour and water. Add to the stew.
Cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes until thick and well cooked.
Remove from fire and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Preheat broiler.
To make marinade, combine garlic, oil, lemon or lime juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in a bowl.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add flavoring and sugar gradually.
Continue beating until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating to mix well.
Add half of flour with milk.
Beat.
Add rest of flour.
Beat for 2 minutes more.
Pour in 10-inch tube cake pan. Spray Baker's Joy to cake pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.

title: oven-blasted broccoli
directions: Cut florets from broccoli. Peel stalks and cut diagonally into 1-inch pieces. Toss with oil. Place a jellyroll pan in a 500° oven for 5 minutes. Add broccoli in a single layer. Bake at 500°, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Just before serving, drizzle with vinegar.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on crackers or muffins.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture. Stir until moistened.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
(Mix pineapple with bananas immediately to keep them from getting dark.)

title: wa-s-di(ramps)
directions: Ramps grow wild in the mountains.
Fry them with eggs, bacon or ham.

title: scrambles
directions: Melt butter and add all spices.
Pour over cereal and nuts, except pretzels, stirring all the while.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring at about 15 minute intervals.
Last 30 minutes, add the pretzels.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers, breaking cracker where necessary to fit.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Cream shortening and add sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Dissolve soda in applesauce and add alternately with flour mixture.
Add raisins.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk on stove for about 45 to 50 minutes until it makes a soft ball. Take off stove; add vanilla, butter, marshmallows and nuts. Mix with mixer until creamy.
Pour into greased glass pan.
Cook some popcorn and eat it with your fudge. Makes a great snack.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Cook potato; mash and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and roll out.
Fry in deep lard.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.

title: chicken or turkey fajitas
directions: Take chicken or turkey and cut into strips.
Then add peppers and onions cut into strips.
Add Zesty Italian dressing to marinate (overnight is best).

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Mash with margarine and milk until fluffy.
Add onions, cottage cheese, salt and pepper; mix well. Put in 3-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp and cream cheese spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Serve with crackers or spread on party rye.

title: sunburst yam bake
directions: Arrange yams in a circle in a 9-inch pie plate.
Place pineapple in center.
Dot yams and pineapple with marmalade.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: carmen's daffodil dessert
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool.
Combine the cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk in bowl; beat until smooth.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Spread over cake.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix together and
stir
well.
Add
2 small cans frozen lemonade and large
can pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add large bottle
ginger ale and few drops food coloring, same color as jello flavor.
Good and easy.

title: pie dough for fried pies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Let
set
in refrigerator overnight. Remove.
Roll as thin as possible and fill with fruit. Fry in deep fat.
