title: my own barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer over low heat 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to make spread.
Slice all rolls, keeping rolls attached at the sides.
Layer spread on both sides of rolls.
Layer cheese and ham and put rolls together.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then add milk and eggs. Whisk until well blended. Microwave for 5 minutes; stir; microwave 5 minutes more or until thick. Add butter and vanilla; whisk until smooth. Let cool to room temperature. Layer wafers, banana, and pudding mixture. Spread cool whip on top if desired.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Add pie filling mix to milk in a bowl.
Mix slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer, just until blended (about 30 seconds).
Blend in pumpkin spice and 2 cups whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and pecan halves.

title: kielbasa, potato and pepper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice peppers and onions into wedges (or 1 inch pieces).
Halve potatoes; cut kielbasa into 1 inch slices. Put all ingredients in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss with oil.
Cover and bake 60 minutes.

title: danish klejners
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oleo.
Mix in the cream.
Add lemon peel and flour.
Knead together.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into 1 x 2 1/2-inch strips.
Cut 1 inch strip in center.
Pull end through center so it has a twist.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: spellbinders cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Gradually add sugar to butter in bowl, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients, blending well after each ingredient.
Stir in oats, coconut, peanuts and cornflakes.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with bottom of glass dipped in additional crushed cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf with sauce
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, bell pepper, bread crumbs, 1/2 can tomato sauce, pepper and salt together and form loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan in 350° oven.
While this is starting to bake, combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard, brown sugar and water.
Pour over meat loaf and continue to bake for 1 1/2 hours. Baste frequently.

title: mama dot's cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to become room temperature; then blend together very well.
Add few drops of Texas Pete, few dashes red pepper and garlic powder.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small logs.
Roll in chili powder.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; mix in cream cheese while hot. Add other ingredients except pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set slightly, then add pineapple and nuts; pour in 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: salmon strata
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Trim crusts from 5 slices of bread, cut in half diagonally.
Use remaining 3 slices and trimmings to line bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese.
Spread flaked salmon over cheese.
Spread spinach over salmon.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese.
Arrange bread triangles, overlapping on top of cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, onion, spices and salmon liquid.
Pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: flour and salt modeling mixture
directions: Mix equal parts of flour and salt with enough water to make a creamy mixture.
Do not heat.

title: strawberry spread
directions: Beat in blender until smooth. Serve on breads of all kinds.

title: coach taylor's favorite milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars with 1 stick margarine; set aside.
Cream sugar and remaining margarine.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour and salt alternately with combined soda and buttermilk.
Mix candy bars and margarine.
Add candy and margarine and then add vanilla. Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Mix in blender the oil, sugar, ketchup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion.
Store 24 hours.
Pour over remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients in bite-size pieces, place in pan and cover with water.
Add 9 or 10 chicken boullion cubes and cook until tender.
Mix milk and 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls cornstarch together, then add to vegetables and let thicken.
Then add Velveeta cheese grated.
When cheese is melted, it's ready to serve.

title: brownie caramel pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle the pecans into unbaked pastry shell.
Melt the caramels with 2/3 cup condensed milk over low heat.
Spread mixture over the pecans.
Combine egg, margarine and remaining condensed milk.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour chocolate mixture over caramel layer.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes or until the center is set.
Refrigerate.

title: cheddar bacon soup
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/2 cup of the drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside. In large saucepan, cook carrots, celery and onion in reserved bacon drippings until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in bacon, reserving 1/2 cup for garnish.
Soup can be made up to 2 days ahead.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: grandma dyke's graham bread
directions: Mix together
the
flour
and
cracked	wheat, soda and salt. Add raisins to coffee mixture; let cool.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
May
have to set 15 to 30 minutes if appears to be runny.
Place
in
(9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch) greased pans. Line with brown
paper;
grease again.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Test
for
doneness with toothpick.
Don't let it get too dry.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and one-half of sugar together until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
But do not over beat. Add lemon juice and vanilla.

title: one-pot mexican spaghetti
directions: In bowl combine egg, bread crumbs, cheese, chilies, 1/2 teaspoon chili powder and meat.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: winnie the pooh's french toast
directions: Break eggs into bowl.
Add milk and beat with eggbeater.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Let it soak until all liquid is absorbed. Melt butter in large frying pan over medium heat.
Make sure melted butter covers bottom of pan.

title: country corn pudding
directions: Empty corn
into
baking
dish and add flour; mix well. Add eggs, milk,
sugar	and
salt.
Melt
butter and pour over corn mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: steve's steamed italino broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli until it is still crunchy.
Cool broccoli, then refrigerate.
Before serving cold, add a very small amount of Italian salad dressing.
Makes a great hors d'oeuvres.

title: almond brickle sugar cookies
directions: Mix together well, 2 to 3 minutes.
Form into balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes at 350°.

title: savory spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs; add combined milk, butter, onion, parsley, Worcestershire, salt, thyme and nutmeg and mix well. Combine remaining ingredients; add egg mixture and mix well. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 400-45 minutes.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: microwave apple crunch over ice cream
directions: Pour apple pie filling into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chili beef soup
directions: Brown meat.
Can cook onion with meat.
Drain.
Put tomato juice, beans, butter and chili powder in large pan and bring to boil.
Add meat to juice and bean mixture.
Heat to boil and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: nacho fiesta
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef, drain off the oil and fat and set aside.
In a small pan, heat the refried beans on a large plate.
Spread out the tortilla chips.
Spoon the ground beef onto the chips and then the refried beans.
Top off with the shredded cheese.
Place in the oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is thoroughly melted.
(Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.)
Spoon the sour cream onto the center of the chips.
Add salsa sauce, if desired.

title: minnie holt's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix eggs, soup, mayonnaise, butter and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Put in a greased casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients, after well mixed into casserole dish. Pour buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: almond chocolate bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (spreads thin).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Break up chocolate bar and put on top immediately after removing pan from oven (it will melt).
Mash almonds into chocolate.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix well. Serve with assorted fruit.

title: "ada's" macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter.
Layer macaroni, 1 cup grated cheese and sliced pats of butter until all are used up, then pour about 2 cups scalded hot milk over macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tater tot pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in soups.
Heat to boiling. Pour into cake pan.
Lay Tater Tots on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken 20 minutes.
Remove skin and bone.
Shred to small pieces by hand or in food processor.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter and poppy seed. Spread 1/2 of cracker mixture into oblong pan.
Add all of chicken mixture; top off with remaining cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms, celery and onion in butter.
Cook rice according to box directions.
In large casserole dish, combine the sauteed mixture, rice, soup and cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: christmas tea concentrate #4
directions: Brew first 4 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add frozen juice concentrates.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all together and fill ice cream freezer (add as much as needed to fill freezer).
Freeze.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Put in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Remove and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until consistency to spread. Cool before beating.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour with sugar, salt and cinnamon; stir into apples.
Pour into a large pan.
Mix dry ingredients with melted oleo until crumbly.
Place on top of apples and pat down gently. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: souper casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Layer in bottom of large casserole. Pour vegetables over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients; add a little water to make soup creamy.
Pour over vegetables.

title: strawberry preserves deluxe
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar; let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Bring mixture slowly to a boil, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon juice.
Cook rapidly until berries are clear and syrup is thick, about 15 minutes.
Pour into shallow pan; let stand, uncovered, 24 hours in a cool place.
Shake pan occasionally to distribute berries through syrup.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 4 half pints.

title: mini chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare brownie mix as chewy.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
May not use all of mix, depends on thickness.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy, not too long (becomes watery and chips sink).
Gradually add and beat Eagle Brand milk.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips by hand. Pour over hot crust.
Reduce oven; heat to 300°.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Garnish with whipped cream and mini chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt and drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and onion to broccoli.
Mix.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mash Ritz crackers.
Mix together and place on top.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pastichio
directions: Saute the onion in oil. Add the hamburg, tomato sauce and seasonings and simmer. Cook the macaroni and drain.
Melt 1/4 pound butter over the pasta. Set aside. Melt 1/2 pound butter. Slowly add the flour, stirring constantly. Stir in the milk. Let boil, then cool.
Beat the egg yolks and add to the cooled milk mixture. Beat the egg whites and add to the macaroni and stir. Grease a pan and sprinkle the bottom with bread crumbs.
Layer the pasta, cheese and hamburg mixture in the pan. Pour the milk mixture over this and top with the bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Sift in cake flour, sugar, instant coffee, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add water and vanilla. Mix until flour is dampened.
Then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat one minute longer.

title: wine baked chicken with noodles
directions: Saute chicken in butter and garlic.
Sprinkle with salt. Combine tomatoes, sauce, wine, parsley, oregano, pepper, fennel seed and cloves.
Pour over chicken.
Add lemon on slices.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Ten minutes before chicken is done, cook 1 package of noodles.
Drain.
Remove chicken to heated serving dish.
Stir noodles into chicken liquid.
Stir in cheese. Arrange in a ring around edge of chicken.
Garnish with watercress and serve.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup water. Sift flour and salt together. Mix with 1 cup water, then add water with yeast and sugar. Add melted shortening or fat. Knead well; roll out and cut in shape. Put in greased pan. Let rise 3 to 4 hours and bake in hot oven at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: hot peppers
directions: USE RUBBER GLOVES!
Wash and dry banana peppers, remove seeds and cut into strips or rings.
Pack firmly into jar.
Mix the solution together.
Place 1 or 2 cloves of garlic in each jar then pour solution over peppers.
Remove bubbles with a knife.
Put 1 Tbsp of pure olive oil on top of each jar and seal.
Ready to eat in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press mixture evenly into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Make hamburger, green pepper and onion into balls and brown. Mix together the cream of mushroom soup and cream of celery soup with one cup of milk.
Mix real well.
Drain grease from meatballs and put meatballs into soup mixture and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Mix ingredients
and spread over sliced fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix.
Spread over crust.
Beat 3 cups of milk and 2 small packages instant chocolate pudding.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts. Chill.

title: chicken parmesan sandwiches
directions: Cook chicken patties according to directions on package (preferably in the oven).
During the last minute of baking, place cheese on top of chicken. Place chicken on rolls and top with 2 tablespoons spaghetti sauce. Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Put rice in 13 x 9 inch pan. Pour milk over it.
Place chicken over rice.
Put all soups and butter and chicken broth in pan.
Heat till butter melts.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with foil, while cooking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water until tender.
Drain.
Mix in a bowl eggs, mayo, soup and cheese.
Mix good.
Fold in broccoli. Sprinkle Ritz crumbs on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until golden brown).
Do not cover.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and milk.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 11 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain and reserve for later use.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, lemon juice, vanilla and almond; stir well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into baked crust.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water for 5 minutes, until they pop, then take off flame.
Add sugar.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Dissolve Jell-O in cooked berries and sugar.
Let cool, not set, then add pineapple (diced), celery and a few chopped walnuts.
Put in mold overnight.
Serve with spiced peach or slices of canned peaches and water cress on bed of greens.

title: barbecue ham slice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over ham.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn a few times.
Grill over low coals or low heat for 5 minutes a side or longer if thick.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix butter or margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O.
Mix until Jell-O dissolves. Add frozen strawberries.
Let set 5 minutes in refrigerator.

title: honey almond squares
directions: Bake cake as directed on
package
in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Cream the
cheese
and
gradually add honey; beat until smooth.
Spread cream
cheese
mixture
on top of cooled cake and sprinkle
with
almonds.
Store in refrigerator.
Cut into squares as desired.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime 24 hours; drain and rinse well. Soak in clear water 4 hours. Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers that have been drained. Let stand overnight. Cook until clear. Add green food coloring to desired amount. Simmer 35 minutes. Seal in jars.

title: jello cake
directions: Boil water, add sugar and Jell-O and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until slightly chilled (about 40 minutes).
Mix with Carnation milk in blender or mixer until fluffy at high speed. Crush cookies and put on bottom of 12 x 8-inch pan.
Add mixture and top with more crushed cookies.
Put in fridge until completely chilled and firm.
Enjoy!

title: golden grahams s'mores
directions: Grease	rectangular
pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat syrup, margarine and morsels to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from
heat;
stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in bowl;
toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan with
buttered back of spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature up to 2 days. Makes 24 squares.

title: coffee cream cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside to use 1/2 at a time.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and lemon juice. Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 12 minutes. Then turn down to 350° and bake about 30 minutes more.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine cake mix and coconut; cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Lightly press into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Arrange peach slices over crust.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Blend sour cream and egg; pour over all.
Bake at 350° just until sour cream is set, about 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: beef dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and Worcestershire sauce in large mixing bowl.
Stir until creamy.
In separate bowl, blend remaining ingredients, then combine with cream cheese mixture. Chill.

title: stroganoff for a crowd
directions: Partially freeze meat for easier cutting.
Cut meat into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
In large Dutch oven or kettle, brown the meat, one pound at a time, in hot shortening.
Return all meat to kettle or Dutch oven; sprinkle with pepper.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Combine soup, beef broth and tomato paste; blend until smooth.
Add to meat; cover, simmering until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir some of the hot mixture into sour cream; return to meat mixture and heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve meat over hot noodles.
Serves 24.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cube bread and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with mushrooms and/or meats.
Melt cheese and margarine in saucepan and pour over bread.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and dry mustard together. Pour over bread in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered, sitting in a cookie sheet filled with water.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
In a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer pork chops, potatoes (cut in thin slices) and onion (cut in thin slices).
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes on 350° or until meat is done.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: cho-mint ice tea
directions: Place 4 cups boiling water over tea bags.
Let steep 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags; add sugar and chocolate syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool; chill to serve.
Place one scoop of mint chocolate chip ice cream in each glass.
Add tea base; top off with 2 tablespoons club soda per glass.
Serves 6.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon over broken pretzel pieces.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time, beating each in thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Bake in 3 layers at 375° about 30 minutes.
Fill and frost as desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Cover meat with sauce before baking.

title: oatmeal banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use paper liners or grease muffin tins.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well in blender and pour into 2 quart freezer container. Freeze overnight. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving. After placing mixture in punch bowl pour the 2 liter sprite over fruit mixture.

title: mid-west apple dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub in fat.
Add milk, all at one time. Stir with a fork.
Turn out on floured board and turn a few times. Roll out thinly and line a baking dish or casserole
with half of dough.
Mix apples (thinly sliced) with sugar, a little cinnamon and nutmeg and a few drops of lemon juice.
Put into lined dish. Cover with remaining pastry.
Pinch crust together.

title: breakfast sticky buns
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle pecans over the bottom. Evenly shake the package of pudding over the nuts.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the dry pudding. Evenly place the rolls in the pan. Cook the butter and sugar until it bubbles and pour over the rolls.
Put the pan in a cold oven overnight to rise.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes. When done, turn upside down immediately on a serving dish.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In small bowl, combine vanilla pudding and 1 cup milk.
Let thicken; add peanut butter.
Mix together.
Add 8 ounce Cool Whip. Put in crust.
Let set while preparing chocolate pudding.

title: texas scramble
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in a large paper bag.
Pour oil over top of dry ingredients and shake until well mixed.
Spread in large flat pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
In large bowl, mix beef and onions with cooked noodles.
Add soups and cheese.
Mix well. Place in sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: venison stew(from a 100-year-old recipe)
directions: Dredge venison in flour and salt.
Melt bacon fat in a soup kettle and brown venison pieces in fat.
Add sugar, onions and cider.
Cover kettle and simmer for 2 hours.
Add water if kettle begins to steam away liquid.
Add stock and vegetables and cook over medium heat 25 minutes until vegetables are tender.
You can mix a paste of flour and water and stir into broth if you need to do this to thicken.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Takes about 1/2 hour with canned tomatoes and beans.

title: mother's old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, blend margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture; mix to blend.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Flatten with floured fork to 2-inch diameter. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet; remove to cooling rack.
Yield:
3 dozen large cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat first six ingredients at low speed until mixed.
Blend in pumpkin, water, baking soda and flour.
Pour batter into greased mini loaf pans or mini Bundt pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and drop on cooling rack.

title: peppermint ice cream
directions: Place candy between 2 sheets of waxed paper; crush with a rolling pin until very fine.
Soak in the milk for 1 hour, stirring from time to time.
Mix with the whipping cream.
Pour into freezing trays; freeze.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss well.
Cover and chill.

title: pina colada cake
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer, combine cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and cream of coconut; beat well.
Pour in 3 greased and floured cake pans or one oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: howard johnson's cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.
Let cool.

title: sensational layered salad
directions: Combine neufchatel cheese and blue cheese, mixing until well blended. Add mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and chives; mix well. Combine greens and carrots. Combine ham and green peppers. In a 3 quart bowl, layer greens mixture, tomatoes and meat mixture. Spread cheese mixture over meat mixture to seal. Cover; chill several hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Melt butter with olive oil and brown chicken until golden brown.
As pieces brown, place in pot which has been on stove with very low heat and cover.
Remove excess chicken fat from pan, add onions and mushrooms.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Add wine.
Pour this mixture into pot with chicken and simmer for 40 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Make a well in mixture. Add eggs, oil and carrots; beat together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: broiled cheese sandwich
directions: Cut bacon to have 3 half pieces; partially cook.
Place toast on rack of broiler pan.
Cover with cheese.
Heat under broiler until cheese starts to melt.
Remove from oven.
Cover cheese with tomato.
Place bacon on top and broil until bacon is cooked. Serve hot.

title: italian sausage spaghetti
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce in frying pan, bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low. Add tomato paste to sauce, stirring till dissolved. Add pack of spaghetti powder to sauce, stirring thoroughly.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In 11 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam, layer kraut, dressing, butter, corned beef and Swiss cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then top with biscuits.
Bake another 15 minutes, until browned.

title: honey chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and honey; add eggs and vanilla.
Measure flour and soda; mix.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: iowa city chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a double boiler; stir until blended.
Set aside and let cool.
Whip 1 cup of whipping cream and fold cooled chocolate mixture into it.
Pour into crust.
Keep refrigerated.
Takes a while to set.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: peach crunch
directions: Spread peaches evenly in 8 or 9-inch baking dish; add juice. Sprinkle sugar over peaches; sprinkle (dry) cake mix over peaches and juice.
Use stick margarine, sliced in very thin slices, and try to cover all of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef
and
onions.
Drain grease and mix with taco mix.
Mix together soup, tomato sauce, chile peppers and taco
sauce
(optional).
Add
to
ground
beef
mixture. Crumble Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour other ingredients on top and spread cheese over this.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Place broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Cover with cheese.
Crush crackers and mix with butter. Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Place jello in mixing bowl; add hot water to dissolve jello. Add melted butter.
Let cool somewhat.
Add cake mix and eggs; beat about 25 or 30 strokes.
Bake at 325°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften and mix cheese and butter together in food processor. Mix flour and cayenne pepper together and mix into cheese mixture a little at a time.
Roll out and cut into strips.
(A pizza cutter works good.)
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until a very light brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl. Add egg, water and milk. Mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry until brown.

title: the chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla together in a large bowl.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, salt and soda together.
Add this flour mixture to creamed mixture and blend well.
Add chocolate chips and chopped pecans and stir gently.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place English muffins butter side down in a 9 X 13 baking dish.
Spread sausage over muffins.
Whip together eggs and sour cream.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over egg mixture.
Sprinkle chilies over cheese.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: ham casserole
directions: Pierce box of peas in several places and microwave for 5 minutes; set aside.
Combine ham, cheese, soup, milk and mustard in a 3-quart glass casserole.
Add noodles and peas. Stir to blend.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking.

title: beef and mushrooms filled gougere
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef in medium skillet. Drain.
Add mushrooms, onions, garlic and thyme.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: date bars
directions: Melt Spry and cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Combine dates and nuts with flour and all.
Mix well.
Beat eggs until light; add melted Spry.
Add to date mixture and stir thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut and dust with powdered sugar.

title: stew meat old fashion way
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper, garlic salt, basil and thyme in a bag well; add stew meat and shake until coated well.
Place stew meat in hot oil in large skillet or Dutch oven; cook until brown and add onion and beef broth.
Cover tightly and simmer slowly until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add mushrooms the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice. Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese bread
directions: Blend all ingredients; spread onto French bread. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: green pasta with shrimp and clams
directions: Shuck clams and reserve juice.
Discard shells.
(Should have approximately 3/4 cup raw clams and 1 cup liquid.) Chop clams coarsely and set aside.
Bring water to a boil and salt to taste. Add pasta.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes after water returns to boil. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup water.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet and add garlic.
Cook briefly without browning.
Add pepper flakes, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring shrimp and shaking skillet for about 1 minute.
Add clams.
Cook about 15 seconds. Add basil leaves and parsley.
Stir to blend and remove from heat. Pour pasta into a kettle and add reserved clam juice.
Heat thoroughly.
Add reserved water and butter.
Pour shrimp and clam mix into pasta; toss to blend.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: golden rod
directions: In medium saucepan, hard-boil 6 eggs (10 to 15 minutes). Meanwhile, in large saucepan, on medium heat, melt butter.
Using wire whisk, whisk in enough flour to soak up all of butter (will make small balls).
Add 2 cups milk, stir constantly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sauce will thicken.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Use a fork to remove yolk.
Place yolk in a strainer/colander (very small grade).
Chop egg whites and place in sauce.
Toast bread and place on plates.
Pour sauce over toast.
Using a spoon, push yolks through strainer over top of toast.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: In 3-quart (approximately) flowerpot, sprinkle half of the pulverized Oreos evenly across bottom.
With electric mixer, combine cream cheese, pudding and half of the milk called for on the pudding box in large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip thoroughly.
Pour mixture evenly over Oreos, then sprinkle remaining Oreos over top.
"Plant" artificial flowers and garnish with gummy worms (optional).
Stick tail ends slightly into Oreo crumbs.
Serves 6 to 8.
Be careful, it's addictive.

title: cheese cache chicken
directions: Cut pocket in each chicken breast (do not cut through).
Place strip of cheese and a sprig of sage in each pocket.
Chill.

title: helen's cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix well . Add 1 cup juice and water.
Add drained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts.
Chill until partially set. Add celery and apples.
Fold in half of yogurt.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 6-cup ring.
Chill until firm.
Spread yogurt evenly over firm gelatin.
Gently spoon the remaining gelatin mixture on top of the yogurt.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sweet & sour meat balls
directions: Drain pineapple juice set aside. Mix ground beef, onion and pineapple. Make into balls. Fry until done. In a small pan mix pineapple juice, vinegar, brown sugar, corn starch and soy sauce, bring to a boil. Pour over meat balls. Serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: This may be mixed in a 3-quart covered bowl or in individual bowls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham ball
directions: Chop the ham and onion into bite size pieces.
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all of the onion and about 1/2 of the ham with the cream cheese.
Mix the Accent into mixture.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Sprinkle the rest of the ham over the ball. Serve with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Set in larger pan of water.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and gently form into balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: flat bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add milk and oil; mix well. Roll 1 tablespoon of dough very thin on well floured pastry cloth to dinner plate size.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 3 minutes; turn over and bake 2 to 4 minutes more, until crisp golden brown.
Bake at 375°.
Cool on cooling rack.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate-potato cake
directions: Stir
together
flour,
cocoa,
baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl cream shortening and sugar until
light.
Add
eggs
and beat until fluffy.
Add potatoes and vanilla;
mix
until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with
milk.
Stir
in
nuts.
Pour
into
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar, then add eggs and melted chocolate and flavorings.
Blend in flour, powder, soda and salt. Chill in refrigerator.
Roll balls of dough in sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, cook ham, garlic and onion in butter until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, rice, sugar and all spices.
Cover and cook until rice is tender (15 to 20 minutes). Add shrimp, olives and peppers.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes to desired thickness.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spiced hush puppies
directions: Rub bowl with garlic.
Place corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add eggs and enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Add onion and mix well. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator until batter becomes spongy.
Heat shortening to 375°.
Drop batter from a tablespoon and fry 4 to 5 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper.
The large amount of baking powder gives a puff ball lightness.
Don't use self-rising flour or corn meal. If
you do, cut amount of baking powder.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender; drain well. Place half of the toast in a baking dish.
Layer half of the onions and half of the cheese over toast.
Repeat layers.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: no fat cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, corn and egg and mix well.
Pour into a 8 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple cake(gale's)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Check in 35 minutes to see if it needs additional cooking.

title: divinity
directions: Combine and cook until hardened ball forms in water. Gradually mix syrup into prepared egg whites.
Add to and mix for awhile until mixture loses some of its gloss, then add pecans and blend with spoon until nearly hardened.
Pour into buttered dish. When set, cut into squares.
